INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('755', '1', '2019-06-17 16:51:30', '2019-06-17 09:51:30', '<h2>Business Status</h2>		\n		<p>Before you register you need to choose your business status carefully as it can be difficult to change, once you have registered</p>		\n		<p><strong>SOLE PROPRIETORSHIP</strong></p><p>Registering as a sole proprietorship means that one person owns and operates the business. This person owns the whole capital and receives all the profits of the company. It also means that all obligations and liabilities are the responsibility of the proprietor. A business registered as a sole proprietorship is considered as a small taxpayer.</p><p>The problem of the sole proprietorship is that you are personally liable for the business but if your business is small and risk of having large debts/liabilities is small, then registering as a sole proprietorship may be the best choice to pay less taxes. Currently, it is difficult for foreigners to be small taxpayers, however they can be registered as a sole proprietorship</p>		\n				Sole ProprietorBest for very small businesses with only one owner\nPartnershipBest for very small businesses with two or more ownersLimited Liability CompanyThe most common form of registration, for small to large businesses. This form of business carries the least liability for the owner/s			\n		<p><strong>PARTNERSHIPS</strong></p><p>Two or more persons together can register as a partnership. This is legally similar to a sole proprietorship, however there are two or more people registered as business owners. It is advised to create a written partnership contract to minimise the risk of any issues that may arise. All the partners are responsible for any debts and obligations.</p><p><strong>PRIVATE LIMITED COMPANY</strong></p><p>This legal company status is what most people think of when they think of registering and is composed of shareholders and directors. Shareholders and directors are not personally liable for the company’s debts. A private limited company is composed of 2 to 30 shareholders.</p><p><strong>FOREIGN BRANCH/SUBSIDIARY</strong></p><p>Even if the company has already registered as another company, its subsidiary, branch or representative office has to register in Cambodia. There are three possibilities:</p><ul><li>Create a subsidiary of the foreign parent. It’s a limited company with 51% or more owned by the foreign company</li><li>A branch office can operate to conduct a particular activity. Then, it is the same entity as the parent company, so the parent company is liable for its debts and obligations.</li><li>A representative office can be implemented but cannot buy or sell on the Cambodian territory. This status only permits to make the sourcing of local goods and services easier or to get information for the parent company.</li></ul>', 'Business Status', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'business-status', '', '', '2019-06-24 16:39:57', '2019-06-24 09:39:57', '', '0', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/?page_id=755', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('756', '1', '2019-06-17 17:01:08', '2019-06-17 10:01:08', '<h2>Business Status</h2>		\n		<p>Before you register you need to choose your business status carefully as it can be difficult to change, once you have registered</p>		\n		<p><strong>SOLE PROPRIETORSHIP</strong></p><p>Registering as a sole proprietorship means that one person owns and operates the business. This person owns the whole capital and receives all the profits of the company. It also means that all obligations and liabilities are the responsibility of the proprietor. A business registered as a sole proprietorship is considered as a small taxpayer.</p><p>The problem of the sole proprietorship is that you are personally liable for the business but if your business is small and risk of having large debts/liabilities is small, then registering as a sole proprietorship may be the best choice to pay less taxes. Currently, it is difficult for foreigners to be small taxpayers, however they can be registered as a sole proprietorship</p><p>Download our checklist here</p><p><strong><img src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/GDT-logo-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></strong><strong style=\"letter-spacing: 0px;\">General Department of Tax</strong></p><ul><li>Know if you are a small, medium or large taxpayer</li><li>Collected all the documents</li><li>Register at the General Department of Tax</li></ul>		\n			<h4>Spread the word</h4>		\n							<a href=\"www.facebook.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n				</a>', 'registering a business checklist', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '755-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-17 17:01:08', '2019-06-17 10:01:08', '', '755', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/17/755-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('757', '1', '2019-06-17 17:01:09', '2019-06-17 10:01:09', '<h2>Business Status</h2>		\n		<p>Before you register you need to choose your business status carefully as it can be difficult to change, once you have registered</p>		\n		<p><strong>SOLE PROPRIETORSHIP</strong></p><p>Registering as a sole proprietorship means that one person owns and operates the business. This person owns the whole capital and receives all the profits of the company. It also means that all obligations and liabilities are the responsibility of the proprietor. A business registered as a sole proprietorship is considered as a small taxpayer.</p><p>The problem of the sole proprietorship is that you are personally liable for the business but if your business is small and risk of having large debts/liabilities is small, then registering as a sole proprietorship may be the best choice to pay less taxes. Currently, it is difficult for foreigners to be small taxpayers, however they can be registered as a sole proprietorship</p>		\n				Sole ProprietorBest for very small businesses with only one owner\nPartnershipBest for very small businesses with one or two more ownersLimited Liability CompanyThe most common form of registration, for small to large businesses. This form of business carries the least liability for the owner/s			\n		<p><strong>PARTNERSHIPS</strong></p><p>Two or more persons together can register as a partnership. This is legally similar to a sole proprietorship, however there are two or more people registered as business owners. It is advised to create a written partnership contract to minimise the risk of any issues that may arise. All the partners are responsible for any debts and obligations.</p><p><strong>PRIVATE LIMITED COMPANY</strong></p><p>This legal company status is what most people think of when they think of registering and is composed of shareholders and directors. Shareholders and directors are not personally liable for the company’s debts. A private limited company is composed of 2 to 30 shareholders.</p><p><strong>FOREIGN BRANCH/SUBSIDIARY</strong></p><p>Even if the company has already registered as another company, its subsidiary, branch or representative office has to register in Cambodia. There are three possibilities:</p><ul><li>Create a subsidiary of the foreign parent. It’s a limited company with 51% or more owned by the foreign company</li><li>A branch office can operate to conduct a particular activity. Then, it is the same entity as the parent company, so the parent company is liable for its debts and obligations.</li><li>A representative office can be implemented but cannot buy or sell on the Cambodian territory. This status only permits to make the sourcing of local goods and services easier or to get information for the parent company.</li></ul>		\n			<h4>Spread the word</h4>		\n							<a href=\"www.facebook.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n				</a>', 'registering a business checklist', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '755-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-17 17:01:09', '2019-06-17 10:01:09', '', '755', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/17/755-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('758', '1', '2019-06-17 17:01:49', '2019-06-17 10:01:49', '<h2>Business Status</h2>\nBefore you register you need to choose your business status carefully as it can be difficult to change, once you have registered\n\n<strong>SOLE PROPRIETORSHIP</strong>\n\nRegistering as a sole proprietorship means that one person owns and operates the business. This person owns the whole capital and receives all the profits of the company. It also means that all obligations and liabilities are the responsibility of the proprietor. A business registered as a sole proprietorship is considered as a small taxpayer.\n\nThe problem of the sole proprietorship is that you are personally liable for the business but if your business is small and risk of having large debts/liabilities is small, then registering as a sole proprietorship may be the best choice to pay less taxes. Currently, it is difficult for foreigners to be small taxpayers, however they can be registered as a sole proprietorship\n\nSole ProprietorBest for very small businesses with only one owner\nPartnershipBest for very small businesses with one or two more ownersLimited Liability CompanyThe most common form of registration, for small to large businesses. This form of business carries the least liability for the owner/s\n\n<strong>PARTNERSHIPS</strong>\n\nTwo or more persons together can register as a partnership. This is legally similar to a sole proprietorship, however there are two or more people registered as business owners. It is advised to create a written partnership contract to minimise the risk of any issues that may arise. All the partners are responsible for any debts and obligations.\n\n<strong>PRIVATE LIMITED COMPANY</strong>\n\nThis legal company status is what most people think of when they think of registering and is composed of shareholders and directors. Shareholders and directors are not personally liable for the company’s debts. A private limited company is composed of 2 to 30 shareholders.\n\n<strong>FOREIGN BRANCH/SUBSIDIARY</strong>\n\nEven if the company has already registered as another company, its subsidiary, branch or representative office has to register in Cambodia. There are three possibilities:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Create a subsidiary of the foreign parent. It’s a limited company with 51% or more owned by the foreign company</li>\n 	<li>A branch office can operate to conduct a particular activity. Then, it is the same entity as the parent company, so the parent company is liable for its debts and obligations.</li>\n 	<li>A representative office can be implemented but cannot buy or sell on the Cambodian territory. This status only permits to make the sourcing of local goods and services easier or to get information for the parent company.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Spread the word</h4>\n<a href=\"www.facebook.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n</a>', 'Business status', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '755-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-17 17:01:49', '2019-06-17 10:01:49', '', '755', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/17/755-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('759', '1', '2019-06-17 17:04:39', '2019-06-17 10:04:39', '<h2>Business Status</h2>		\n		<p>Before you register you need to choose your business status carefully as it can be difficult to change, once you have registered</p>		\n		<p><strong>SOLE PROPRIETORSHIP</strong></p><p>Registering as a sole proprietorship means that one person owns and operates the business. This person owns the whole capital and receives all the profits of the company. It also means that all obligations and liabilities are the responsibility of the proprietor. A business registered as a sole proprietorship is considered as a small taxpayer.</p><p>The problem of the sole proprietorship is that you are personally liable for the business but if your business is small and risk of having large debts/liabilities is small, then registering as a sole proprietorship may be the best choice to pay less taxes. Currently, it is difficult for foreigners to be small taxpayers, however they can be registered as a sole proprietorship</p>		\n				Sole ProprietorBest for very small businesses with only one owner\nPartnershipBest for very small businesses with two or more ownersLimited Liability CompanyThe most common form of registration, for small to large businesses. This form of business carries the least liability for the owner/s			\n		<p><strong>PARTNERSHIPS</strong></p><p>Two or more persons together can register as a partnership. This is legally similar to a sole proprietorship, however there are two or more people registered as business owners. It is advised to create a written partnership contract to minimise the risk of any issues that may arise. All the partners are responsible for any debts and obligations.</p><p><strong>PRIVATE LIMITED COMPANY</strong></p><p>This legal company status is what most people think of when they think of registering and is composed of shareholders and directors. Shareholders and directors are not personally liable for the company’s debts. A private limited company is composed of 2 to 30 shareholders.</p><p><strong>FOREIGN BRANCH/SUBSIDIARY</strong></p><p>Even if the company has already registered as another company, its subsidiary, branch or representative office has to register in Cambodia. There are three possibilities:</p><ul><li>Create a subsidiary of the foreign parent. It’s a limited company with 51% or more owned by the foreign company</li><li>A branch office can operate to conduct a particular activity. Then, it is the same entity as the parent company, so the parent company is liable for its debts and obligations.</li><li>A representative office can be implemented but cannot buy or sell on the Cambodian territory. This status only permits to make the sourcing of local goods and services easier or to get information for the parent company.</li></ul>		\n			<h4>Spread the word</h4>		\n							<a href=\"www.facebook.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n				</a>', 'Business status', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '755-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-17 17:04:39', '2019-06-17 10:04:39', '', '755', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/17/755-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('760', '1', '2019-06-18 11:46:57', '2019-06-18 04:46:57', '<h2>Documents &amp; Prerequisites</h2>		\n		<p>Before you begin the registration process its important you have all the documents ready. This will make the entire process much easier and smoother</p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"100\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/6.-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure><h3>Memorandum &amp; Articles of Association</h3><p>We recommend for this you seek advice, however if you want to complete it yourself, see our template here</p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"100\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/2.-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure><h3>Three company names</h3><p>In order of preference in both Khmer &amp; English </p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"100\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/4.-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure><h3>Proof of Location</h3><p>Property tax receipt and a photo of your building</p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"100\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/5.-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure><h3>Scanned copies of ID for all shareholders</h3><p>Khmer ID or Passports<br>10 passport photographs, signed on the back</p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"100\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1.-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure><h3>Employee Details</h3><p>A digital copy of employee details, see our template here </p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"100\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/3.-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure><h3>Directors Consent</h3><p>A digital copy of Directors consent, see our template here</p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"512\" height=\"512\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-bank-account-money-computer-icons-blue-bank-icon-in-flat-style-with-the-building-fac-5ab080827e7702.906624551521516674518.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-bank-account-money-computer-icons-blue-bank-icon-in-flat-style-with-the-building-fac-5ab080827e7702.906624551521516674518.png 512w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-bank-account-money-computer-icons-blue-bank-icon-in-flat-style-with-the-building-fac-5ab080827e7702.906624551521516674518-150x150.png 150w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-bank-account-money-computer-icons-blue-bank-icon-in-flat-style-with-the-building-fac-5ab080827e7702.906624551521516674518-300x300.png 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-bank-account-money-computer-icons-blue-bank-icon-in-flat-style-with-the-building-fac-5ab080827e7702.906624551521516674518-400x400.png 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-bank-account-money-computer-icons-blue-bank-icon-in-flat-style-with-the-building-fac-5ab080827e7702.906624551521516674518-367x367.png 367w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-bank-account-money-computer-icons-blue-bank-icon-in-flat-style-with-the-building-fac-5ab080827e7702.906624551521516674518-85x85.png 85w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-bank-account-money-computer-icons-blue-bank-icon-in-flat-style-with-the-building-fac-5ab080827e7702.906624551521516674518-50x50.png 50w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></figure><h3>Bank Account</h3><p>Once you have registered with the MoC you need to open a business bank account</p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"512\" height=\"512\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-computer-icons-investment-payment-bank-money-money-icon-png-5ab065b43cec57.4598047615215098122496.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-computer-icons-investment-payment-bank-money-money-icon-png-5ab065b43cec57.4598047615215098122496.png 512w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-computer-icons-investment-payment-bank-money-money-icon-png-5ab065b43cec57.4598047615215098122496-150x150.png 150w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-computer-icons-investment-payment-bank-money-money-icon-png-5ab065b43cec57.4598047615215098122496-300x300.png 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-computer-icons-investment-payment-bank-money-money-icon-png-5ab065b43cec57.4598047615215098122496-400x400.png 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-computer-icons-investment-payment-bank-money-money-icon-png-5ab065b43cec57.4598047615215098122496-367x367.png 367w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-computer-icons-investment-payment-bank-money-money-icon-png-5ab065b43cec57.4598047615215098122496-85x85.png 85w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-computer-icons-investment-payment-bank-money-money-icon-png-5ab065b43cec57.4598047615215098122496-50x50.png 50w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></figure><h3>Proof of Capital</h3><p>Once you have opened your business bank account, you need a receipt from the bank confirming your initial capital</p>		\n			<h3>Confused? We can Help </h3>		\n							\"Ngeay Ngeay has been great for me to be able to find all the information related to running a business in Cambodia and in particular information regarding tax responsibility, it is worded in simple language that I can understand.\"\n							<img width=\"459\" height=\"459\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dai-khmer.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dai-khmer.png 459w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dai-khmer-150x150.png 150w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dai-khmer-300x300.png 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dai-khmer-400x400.png 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dai-khmer-367x367.png 367w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Dai-khmer-85x85.png 85w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp