INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('925', '1', '2019-06-18 23:09:53', '2019-06-18 16:09:53', '<h2>Registering with the General Department of Tax</h2>		\n		<p>To register with the tax department you need to go to the National Tax School, level 6</p>		\n		<p><strong>Tax Registration</strong></p>\n<p>You have 2 weeks once your application is approved to go to the General Department of Taxation and register.</p>\n<p>You need to bring all the documents necessary for tax registration. If your business needs to import/export, you will need to ensure you tell the tax department and get an export patent.&nbsp;</p><p>The registration process takes place at the National Tax School Building, level 6.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Once registered you will receive:</p>\n<p>the Taxpayer Identification Number : this is the number which refers you as a taxpayer with the authorities</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the Patent tax</li>\n<li>the VAT tax.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Cost of tax registration :</p>\n<p>$200 for registration, $300 for tax patent</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The National Tax School can be found here</p>\n<p></p>		\n			<iframe frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?q=National%20tax%20school%2C%20phnom%20penh&amp;t=m&amp;z=12&amp;output=embed&amp;iwloc=near\" aria-label=\"National tax school, phnom penh\"></iframe>', 'registering  with GDT', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'register-gdt', '', '', '2019-07-31 09:46:51', '2019-07-31 02:46:51', '', '0', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/?page_id=925', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('926', '1', '2019-06-18 23:14:12', '2019-06-18 16:14:12', '<h2>Business Status</h2>		\n		<p>Before you register you need to choose your business status carefully as it can be difficult to change, once you have registered</p>		\n		<p><strong>SOLE PROPRIETORSHIP</strong></p><p>Registering as a sole proprietorship means that one person owns and operates the business. This person owns the whole capital and receives all the profits of the company. It also means that all obligations and liabilities are the responsibility of the proprietor. A business registered as a sole proprietorship is considered as a small taxpayer.</p><p>The problem of the sole proprietorship is that you are personally liable for the business but if your business is small and risk of having large debts/liabilities is small, then registering as a sole proprietorship may be the best choice to pay less taxes. Currently, it is difficult for foreigners to be small taxpayers, however they can be registered as a sole proprietorship</p>		\n				Sole ProprietorBest for very small businesses with only one owner\nPartnershipBest for very small businesses with two or more ownersLimited Liability CompanyThe most common form of registration, for small to large businesses. This form of business carries the least liability for the owner/s			\n		<p><strong>PARTNERSHIPS</strong></p><p>Two or more persons together can register as a partnership. This is legally similar to a sole proprietorship, however there are two or more people registered as business owners. It is advised to create a written partnership contract to minimise the risk of any issues that may arise. All the partners are responsible for any debts and obligations.</p><p><strong>PRIVATE LIMITED COMPANY</strong></p><p>This legal company status is what most people think of when they think of registering and is composed of shareholders and directors. Shareholders and directors are not personally liable for the company’s debts. A private limited company is composed of 2 to 30 shareholders.</p><p><strong>FOREIGN BRANCH/SUBSIDIARY</strong></p><p>Even if the company has already registered as another company, its subsidiary, branch or representative office has to register in Cambodia. There are three possibilities:</p><ul><li>Create a subsidiary of the foreign parent. It’s a limited company with 51% or more owned by the foreign company</li><li>A branch office can operate to conduct a particular activity. Then, it is the same entity as the parent company, so the parent company is liable for its debts and obligations.</li><li>A representative office can be implemented but cannot buy or sell on the Cambodian territory. This status only permits to make the sourcing of local goods and services easier or to get information for the parent company.</li></ul>		\n			<h4>Spread the word</h4>		\n							<a href=\"www.facebook.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n				</a>', 'Business status', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '925-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-18 23:14:12', '2019-06-18 16:14:12', '', '925', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/18/925-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
