INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('932', '1', '2019-06-19 15:44:42', '2019-06-19 08:44:42', '<h2>Why Register?</h2>\nThe rate of unregistered businesses is very high in Cambodia. The&nbsp;Cambodian government has been addressing this issue in recent years and working to make the registration process easier and cheaper. But why should you register?\n\n<strong>Six Reasons Why You Should Register?&nbsp;</strong>\n\n<strong>Peace of Mind</strong>\n\nOne of the most common reasons why businesses come to us to register, is for peace of mind. Having an unregistered business is a constant concern for business owners, as that face the risk of fees and penalties when operating an unregistered business. These fees and penalties vary from monetary fines to the closing down of your business.\n\n<strong>Access to Markets&nbsp;</strong>\n\nThe second most common reason why businesses come to us, is because they have just been turned down by a large customer because they were not registered. Registering your business means you will be more likely to access large contracts and customers and grow your business.\n\nExample: a large client of your business wants you to supply your product to them, but they need to have an invoice with VAT.&nbsp; This is because otherwise registered businesses will have to pay withholding tax on their purchases with is 15% compared with VAT which is 10% and they can offset.\n\n<strong>Improved Access to Finance</strong>\n\nUnless you own land that you can use as collateral, accessing finance from a financial institution can be very difficult for small and medium business owners, this becomes much more difficult if you are not registered. Most banks and investment firms will not invest or loan money to a business that is not registered.\n\n<strong>Improved ability to sell</strong>\n\nIf you are looking to sell your business, it becomes much easier if it is registered as it is clear what the buyer is buying, it is legally protected and there are verifiable financial records. If you are not registered, you may not be able to sell as easily or for as much as the business is worth.\n\n<strong>Protect your business</strong>\n\nThrough registration, your name and business is protected, you will have legal ways of fighting any business that copies your product or branding.\n\n<strong>Protect your business</strong>\n\nBeing an ethical business means protecting your employees through labour rights. By registering you are required to pay NSSF on the behalf of staff, provide fair contracts, and provide annual leave and sick leave. This means that your employees will have job security and feel protected, not only is this good for your employees but is also the basis of a great staff culture and staff retention.\n\nThere are many reasons why you should register your business, but these six reasons are the most common reasons we see at Ngeay Ngeay. If you need help registering, please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:admin@ngeayngeay.co\">admin@ngeayngeay.co</a>', 'Why register', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'business-status-2', '', '', '2019-07-20 09:15:04', '2019-07-20 02:15:04', '', '0', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/?page_id=932', '0', 'page', '', '0');
