INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1277', '1', '2019-06-22 12:55:41', '2019-06-22 05:55:41', '<h2>Contracts</h2>		\n		<p>There are two types of contracts in Cambodian Labor Law, fixed duration contracts (FDC’s) and Unfixed Duration Contracts (UDC’s).</p>		\n		<p><strong>Fixed Duration Contracts</strong></p><p>These contracts are for a fixed term, and can be anywhere up to 2 years in length. After two years the employer can decide to renew the contract or not renew the contract. A fixed term contract must be in writing.</p><p>If the contract finishes, and the employee continues working without a contract, the employee is understood to be on a UDC</p><p>If a fixed term contract expires or is terminated, the employee has the right to severance pay of 5% of total wages over the contract (Article 73). If a FDC is terminated early, the employer is required to payout the entire the value of the contract.</p><p><strong>Unfixed Duration Contracts</strong></p><p>Unfixed duration contracts are for an unspecified amount of time and can be either verbal or written.</p><p>For terminating a UDC  the minimum period of notice is:</p><ul><li>Seven days, if the worker\'s length of continuous service is less than six months;</li><li>Fifteen days, if the worker\'s length of continuous service is from six months to two years;</li><li>One month, if the worker\'s length of continuous service is longer than two years and up to five years.</li><li>Two months, if the worker\'s length of continuous service is longer than five years and up to ten years.</li><li>Three months, if the worker\'s length of continuous service is longer than then years.</li></ul><p>Seniority payments are also applicable to UDC’s. For more information please see the Seniority Payments section</p>', 'Contracts - G', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1153-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 12:55:41', '2019-06-22 05:55:41', '', '1153', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/1153-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1278', '1', '2019-06-22 12:59:55', '2019-06-22 05:59:55', '<h2>Documents &amp; Prerequisites</h2>		\n		<p>Before you begin the registration process its important you have all the documents ready. This will make the entire process much easier and smoother</p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"100\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/6.-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure><h3>Memorandum &amp; Articles of Association</h3><p>We recommend for this you seek advice, however if you want to complete it yourself, see our template here</p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"100\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/2.-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure><h3>Three company names</h3><p>In order of preference in both Khmer &amp; English </p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"100\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/4.-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure><h3>Proof of Location</h3><p>Property tax receipt and a photo of your building</p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"100\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/5.-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure><h3>Scanned copies of ID for all shareholders</h3><p>Khmer ID or Passports<br>10 passport photographs, signed on the back</p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"100\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1.-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure><h3>Employee Details</h3><p>A digital copy of employee details, see our template here </p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"100\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/3.-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></figure><h3>Directors Consent</h3><p>A digital copy of Directors consent, see our template here</p>		\n			<figure><img width=\"512\" height=\"512\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/kisspng-bank-account-money-computer-icons-blue-bank-icon-in-flat-style-with-the-building-fac-5ab080827e7702.906624551521516674518.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co