INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1294', '1', '2019-06-22 16:50:07', '2019-06-22 09:50:07', '<h2>Leave</h2>\nThere are various types of leave that employees are obligated to receive in Cambodia\n\n<strong>Annual Leave</strong>\n\nAnnual leave is provided to all employees once they have completed 1 year of service. Annual leave is on a pro-rata rate, of 18 days after 1 years service, based on a 48 hour work week. If the employee works less than 48 hours, for example, 40 hours, then the employee is provided 15 days of annual leave.\n\nFor every 3 years of service the employee is entitled to an extra day of annual leave per year.\n\n<strong>Weekly Rest</strong>\n\nAll employees are entitled to 24 consecutive hours of rest per week\n\n<strong>Sick Leave</strong>\n\nThe labour law requires a business to provide a sick leave to employees, if they have a letter from a certified doctor for up to 6 months, after 6 months the business can terminate the employee. The rates of pay for the employee during the sick period is as follows:\n<ul>\n 	<li>During the 1st month of illness: 100% of wages,</li>\n 	<li>During the 2nd and 3rd months of illness: 60% of wages,</li>\n 	<li>During the 4th month and longer: no wages paid</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Maternity Leave</strong>\n\nAll women are entitled to maternity leave of 90 days, the employee is entitled to half the wages and benefits.\n\n<strong>Public Holidays</strong>\n\nAll employees are entitled to public holiday leave according the public holiday sub-decree issued by the government. In the case a public holiday is on a Sunday, employees are entitled to take the following Monday off work.\n\nIf businesses are required to open on public holidays, employees can work voluntarily but are entitled to pay of 200% of their normal wage.', 'Leave - G', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1176-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 16:50:07', '2019-06-22 09:50:07', '', '1176', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/1176-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1295', '1', '2019-06-22 16:50:25', '2019-06-22 09:50:25', '<h2>How to find Start Up Capital</h2>		\n		<p>When we talk to budding entrepreneurs, one of the most common questions we get asked is how can I start a business if I don\'t have any money. Below you will find the most common ways to get startup capital for a new business</p>		\n		<p><strong>Using your own resources</strong></p><p>Many businesses do not need a lot of start up capital, and often your dream business can be scaled down so that you can begin with little money and build your way up. This is also a very good way of testing your target market, and your value proposition. Think about how you can save your money to start a very small business, and use the profits of that to save more to build a bigger business. Often many entrepreneurs in the beginning will have multipe jobs, they will have their normal job as well as run their business until they have enough capital to do their business 100%.</p><p><strong>Family and Friends</strong></p><p>Asking family and friend for money is one of the most common ways entrepreneurs can get started. Again, this will often mean that you have to start a smaller scale business until you can generate enough funds to start a bigger business, but this is a great way to start. </p><p><strong>Grants</strong></p><p>There are many grants that will help fund small businesses, if you have a unique idea then you can look at the many grants that come up in Cambodia to see if your idea fits with those.</p><p><strong>Micro-loans</strong></p><p>Micro-loans are some of the easiest loans to receive in Cambodia and this can be a great way to get started. You need to be very aware of the costs involved and watch out for any hidden costs. See our loan calculator to help you see how much you will pay in interest.</p><p><strong>Investment and Loans</strong></p><p>It is often very difficult to get investment and larger loans for a non-existing business, however it does happen occasionally. If you would like to talk further about investment please contact us at ngeayngeay.co and we can help direct you to investors.</p><p>See our <a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/funding-opportunities/\">Funding Opportunities</a> page for upcoming opportunities for your business</p><p> </p>', 'How to find startup capital', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'leave-2', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:10:29', '2019-07-23 04:10:29', '', '0', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/?page_id=1295', '0', 'page', '', '0');
