INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1299', '1', '2019-06-22 17:01:30', '2019-06-22 10:01:30', '<h2>How to find Start Up Capital</h2>		\n		<p>When we talk to budding entrepreneurs, one of the most common questions we get asked is how can I start a business if I don\'t have any money. Below you will find the most common ways to get startup capital for a new business</p>		\n		<p><strong>Using your own resources</strong></p><p>Many businesses do not need a lot of start up capital, and often your dream business can be scaled down so that you can begin with little money and build your way up. This is also a very good way of testing your target market, and your value proposition. Think about how you can save your money to start a very small business, and use the profits of that to save more to build a bigger business. Often many entrepreneurs in the beginning will have multipe jobs, they will have their normal job as well as run their business until they have enough capital to do their business 100%.</p><p><strong>Family and Friends</strong></p><p>Asking family and friend for money is one of the most common ways entrepreneurs can get started. Again, this will often mean that you have to start a smaller scale business until you can generate enough funds to start a bigger business, but this is a great way to start. </p><p><strong>Grants</strong></p><p>There are many grants that will help fund small businesses, if you have a unique idea then you can look at the many grants that come up in Cambodia to see if your idea fits with those.</p><p><strong>Micro-loans</strong></p><p>Micro-loans are some of the easiest loans to receive in Cambodia and this can be a great way to get started. You need to be very aware of the costs involved and watch out for any hidden costs. See our loan calculator to help you see how much you will pay in interest.</p><p><strong>Investment and Loans</strong></p><p>It is often very difficult to get investment and larger loans for a non-existing business, however it does happen occasionally. If you would like to talk further about investment please contact us at ngeayngeay.co and we can help direct you to investors.</p><p>See our <a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/funding-opportunities/\">Funding Opportunities</a> page for upcoming opportunities for your business</p><p> </p>', 'Leave - G', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1295-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 17:01:30', '2019-06-22 10:01:30', '', '1295', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/1295-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1300', '1', '2019-06-22 17:04:03', '2019-06-22 10:04:03', '<h2>How to find Start Up Capital</h2>\nWhen we talk to budding entrepreneurs, one of the most common questions we get asked is how can I start a business if I don\'t have any money. Below you will find the most common ways to get startup capital for a new business\n\n<strong>Using your own resources</strong>\n\nMany businesses do not need a lot of start up capital, and often your dream business can be scaled down so that you can begin with little money and build your way up. This is also a very good way of testing your target market, and your value proposition. Think about how you can save your money to start a very small business, and use the profits of that to save more to build a bigger business. Often many entrepreneurs in the beginning will have multipe jobs, they will have their normal job as well as run their business until they have enough capital to do their business 100%.\n\n<strong>Family and Friends</strong>\n\nAsking family and friend for money is one of the most common ways entrepreneurs can get started. Again, this will often mean that you have to start a smaller scale business until you can generate enough funds to start a bigger business, but this is a great way to start.&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Grants</strong>\n\nThere are many grants that will help fund small businesses, if you have a unique idea then you can look at the many grants that come up in Cambodia to see if your idea fits with those.\n\n<strong>Micro-loans</strong>\n\nMicro-loans are some of the easiest loans to receive in Cambodia and this can be a great way to get started. You need to be very aware of the costs involved and watch out for any hidden costs. See our loan calculator to help you see how much you will pay in interest.\n\n<strong>Investment and Loans</strong>\n\nIt is often very difficult to get investment and larger loans for a non-existing business, however it does happen occasionally. If you would like to talk further about investment please contact us at ngeayngeay.co and we can help direct you to investors.\n\nSee our <a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/funding-opportunities/\">Funding Opportunities</a> page for upcoming opportunities for your business', 'How to find startup capital', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1295-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 17:04:03', '2019-06-22 10:04:03', '', '1295', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/1295-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
