u would like to talk further about investment please contact us at ngeayngeay.co and we can help direct you to investors.\n\nSee our <a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/funding-opportunities/\">Funding Opportunities</a> page for upcoming opportunities for your business', 'How to find startup capital - G', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1295-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 17:06:26', '2019-06-22 10:06:26', '', '1295', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/1295-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1302', '1', '2019-06-22 17:07:36', '2019-06-22 10:07:36', '<h2>Ministry of Labour Registration</h2>		\n		<p>All business registered with the MoC and General Department of Tax need to be registered with the Ministry of Labour.</p>		\n		<p>To register at the Ministry of Labour you will need</p><ul><li>Tax Patent</li><li>Certificate of Incorporation</li><li>Employee List (see template here)</li><li>Ministry of Labour forms filled out</li></ul><p>Take all the documents to the building called “General Labour” or អគ្គការងារ, on level 3. The general Labour building is at the back on the right.</p><p> </p>		\n			<iframe frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?q=ministry%20of%20labour&amp;t=m&amp;z=14&amp;output=embed&amp;iwloc=near\" aria-label=\"ministry of labour\"></iframe>', 'Ministry of Labour Registration - G', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1180-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 17:07:36', '2019-06-22 10:07:36', '', '1180', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/1180-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1303', '1', '2019-06-22 17:09:33', '2019-06-22 10:09:33', '<h2>Monthly Taxes</h2>		\n		<p>Filing monthly taxes is a complex process for medium and large taxpayers. We highly recommend you hire a professional to assist you</p>		\n		<p>Each month you will have to pay your taxes, this includes your value added tax (VAT), tax on salary, minimum tax on profit, withholding tax and public lighting tax. Additionally you will need to pay your NSSF fees (see here).</p><p>Filing and payment of taxes in Cambodia for medium and large taxpayers is quite complex, we highly recommend that you hire a professional to assist you in this process. However, it is important you understand the basic process, as its your responsibility to ensure that all the taxes are paid correctly.</p><p>For small taxpayers (sole proprietors and partnerships), you only need to fill out one form. The instructions are found on the second page of the form.</p><p>For medium and large taxpayers, there are multiple forms and evidence that is required.</p><p>To file your taxes you need to download the appropriate forms found here. You will need to fill out all the forms and provide the necessary evidence, you need to hand these forms in, with payment to your local tax department for your Khan. Monthly taxes are due on the 20<sup>th</sup> of each month.</p><p><a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/tax-nssf-rates/\">For the latest tax rates, see here.</a></p>', 'Monthly Taxes', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1156-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 17:09:33', '2019-06-22 10:09:33', '', '1156', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/1156-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1304', '1', '2019-06-22 17:10:35', '2019-06-22 10:10:35', '<h2>Monthly Taxes</h2>		\n		<p>Filing monthly taxes is a complex process for medium and large taxpayers. We highly recommend you hire a professional to assist you</p>		\n		<p>Each month you will have to pay your taxes, this includes your value added tax (VAT), tax on salary, minimum tax on profit, withholding tax and public lighting tax. Additionally you will need to pay your NSSF fees (see here).</p><p>Filing and payment of taxes in Cambodia for medium and large taxpayers is quite complex, we highly recommend that you hire a professional to assist you in this process. However, it is important you understand the basic process, as its your responsibility to ensure that all the taxes are paid correctly.</p><p>For small taxpayers (sole proprietors and partnerships), you only need to fill out one form. The instructions are found on the second page of the form.</p><p>For medium and large taxpayers, there are multiple forms and evidence that is required.</p><p>To file your taxes you need to download the appropriate forms found here. You will need to fill out all the forms and provide the necessary evidence, you need to hand these forms in, with payment to your local tax department for your Khan. Monthly taxes are due on the 20<sup>th</sup> of each month.</p><p><a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/tax-nssf-rates/\">For the latest tax rates, see here.</a></p>', 'Monthly Taxes-needs links to tax forms', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1156-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 17:10:35', '2019-06-22 10:10:35', '', '1156', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/1156-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1305', '1', '2019-06-22 17:12:25', '2019-06-22 10:12:25', '<h2>Monthly Tax &amp; NSSF Rates</h2>		\n		<p>Monthly Taxes are due at the 20th of each month, NSSF is due on the 15th of each month</p>		\n		<p><strong>1. Minimum Tax</strong></p><p>Profit tax prepayment:</p><p>Every month, you need to pay the rate of 1% on your turnover of the previous month inclusive of all taxes, except for VAT.</p><p><strong>2. Withholding Tax</strong></p><p>Rental : 10%</p><p>Labour : 15%</p><p><strong>3. Value Added Tax (VAT)</strong></p><p>The standard rate of VAT is 10%. It applies to all supplies, excluding exports and non-taxable supplies. Exported goods from Cambodia and services consumed outside Cambodia are not subject to VAT tax. The VAT is charged to the client and then paid to the government.</p><p><strong>4. Salary Tax and Tax on Fringe Benefit</strong></p><p>A company that has employees has to withhold tax before paying the employees and to pay it to the tax administration the month after the salary is paid. The rate depends on the employee salary, as listed below.</p><p>Monthly salary (Riels) Rate:</p><p>0 – 1,200,000                          0%</p><p>1,200,001 – 2,000,000          5%</p><p>2,000,001 – 8,500,000          10%</p><p>8,500,001 – 12,500,000        15%</p><p>12,500,001 – upwards          20%</p><p>You can download the <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.gdt.project.salarytax2018&amp;hl=en\">Salary Tax 2018 App</a> here, it can calculate your salary tax</p><p><strong>5. Public Lighting Tax</strong></p><p>This is a tax on all alcohol and cigarettes. The rate is 3% of all sales.</p><p><strong>NSSF Rates</strong></p><p>There are two contributions for the National Social Security Fund that are to be made each month by the employer.</p><p><strong>The Occupational Risk Scheme</strong></p><p>The rate for occupational risk is 0.8% of the workers gross wage.</p><p><strong>The Health Care Scheme</strong></p><p>The rate for the Health Care Scheme is 2.6% of the workers gross wage.</p><p>All workers are to be registered with the NSSF within 3 days of beginning employment.</p><p>NSSF payment deadline: 15<sup>th</sup> of each month</p>', 'Tax & NSSF Rates', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1189-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 17:12:25', '2019-06-22 10:12:25', '', '1189', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/1189-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1306', '1', '2019-06-22 17:13:37', '2019-06-22 10:13:37', '<h2>Monthly Tax &amp; NSSF Rates</h2>		\n		<p>Monthly Taxes are due at the 20th of each month, NSSF is due on the 15th of each month</p>		\n		<p><strong>1. Minimum Tax</strong></p><p>Profit tax prepayment:</p><p>Every month, you need to pay the rate of 1% on your turnover of the previous month inclusive of all taxes, except for VAT.</p><p><strong>2. Withholding Tax</strong></p><p>Rental : 10%</p><p>Labour : 15%</p><p><strong>3. Value Added Tax (VAT)</strong></p><p>The standard rate of VAT is 10%. It applies to all supplies, excluding exports and non-taxable supplies. Exported goods from Cambodia and services consumed outside Cambodia are not subject to VAT tax. The VAT is charged to the client and then paid to the government.</p><p><strong>4. Salary Tax and Tax on Fringe Benefit</strong></p><p>A company that has employees has to withhold tax before paying the employees and to pay it to the tax administration the month after the salary is paid. The rate depends on the employee salary, as listed below.</p><p>Monthly salary (Riels) Rate:</p><p>0 – 1,200,000                          0%</p><p>1,200,001 – 2,000,000          5%</p><p>2,000,001 – 8,500,000          10%</p><p>8,500,001 – 12,500,000        15%</p><p>12,500,001 – upwards          20%</p><p>You can download the <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.gdt.project.salarytax2018&amp;hl=en\">Salary Tax 2018 App</a> here, it can calculate your salary tax</p><p><strong>5. Public Lighting Tax</strong></p><p>This is a tax on all alcohol and cigarettes. The rate is 3% of all sales.</p><p><strong>NSSF Rates</strong></p><p>There are two contributions for the National Social Security Fund that are to be made each month by the employer.</p><p><strong>The Occupational Risk Scheme</strong></p><p>The rate for occupational risk is 0.8% of the workers gross wage.</p><p><strong>The Health Care Scheme</strong></p><p>The rate for the Health Care Scheme is 2.6% of the workers gross wage.</p><p>All workers are to be registered with the NSSF within 3 days of beginning employment.</p><p>NSSF payment deadline: 15<sup>th</sup> of each month</p>', 'Tax & NSSF Rates - G', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1189-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 17:13:37', '2019-06-22 10:13:37', '', '1189', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/1189-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
