INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1325', '1', '2019-06-22 17:39:35', '2019-06-22 10:39:35', '<h2>Business Status</h2>		\n		<p>Before you register you need to choose your business status carefully as it can be difficult to change, once you have registered</p>		\n		<p><strong>SOLE PROPRIETORSHIP</strong></p><p>Registering as a sole proprietorship means that one person owns and operates the business. This person owns the whole capital and receives all the profits of the company. It also means that all obligations and liabilities are the responsibility of the proprietor. A business registered as a sole proprietorship is considered as a small taxpayer.</p><p>The problem of the sole proprietorship is that you are personally liable for the business but if your business is small and risk of having large debts/liabilities is small, then registering as a sole proprietorship may be the best choice to pay less taxes. Currently, it is difficult for foreigners to be small taxpayers, however they can be registered as a sole proprietorship</p>		\n				Sole ProprietorBest for very small businesses with only one owner\nPartnershipBest for very small businesses with two or more ownersLimited Liability CompanyThe most common form of registration, for small to large businesses. This form of business carries the least liability for the owner/s			\n		<p><strong>PARTNERSHIPS</strong></p><p>Two or more persons together can register as a partnership. This is legally similar to a sole proprietorship, however there are two or more people registered as business owners. It is advised to create a written partnership contract to minimise the risk of any issues that may arise. All the partners are responsible for any debts and obligations.</p><p><strong>PRIVATE LIMITED COMPANY</strong></p><p>This legal company status is what most people think of when they think of registering and is composed of shareholders and directors. Shareholders and directors are not personally liable for the company’s debts. A private limited company is composed of 2 to 30 shareholders.</p><p><strong>FOREIGN BRANCH/SUBSIDIARY</strong></p><p>Even if the company has already registered as another company, its subsidiary, branch or representative office has to register in Cambodia. There are three possibilities:</p><ul><li>Create a subsidiary of the foreign parent. It’s a limited company with 51% or more owned by the foreign company</li><li>A branch office can operate to conduct a particular activity. Then, it is the same entity as the parent company, so the parent company is liable for its debts and obligations.</li><li>A representative office can be implemented but cannot buy or sell on the Cambodian territory. This status only permits to make the sourcing of local goods and services easier or to get information for the parent company.</li></ul>', 'Business Status - G', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '755-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 17:39:35', '2019-06-22 10:39:35', '', '755', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/755-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1326', '1', '2019-06-22 17:42:51', '2019-06-22 10:42:51', '<h2>Registering a Business</h2>		\n		<p>What you need to know to register a business in Cambodia</p>		\n			<h2>Ministry of Commerce</h2>		\n				<h3>\n					Know your Business Status\n				</h3>\n				<p>There are a variety of business statuses in Cambodia, the most common are sole proprietor, partnership and limited liability companies. Read our article for more information</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/business-status/\" role=\"button\">\n						Read more here\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-1024x683.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-300x200.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-768x512.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-640x427.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-400x267.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-367x245.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					Collect all the documents <br><br>\nand prerequisites\n				</h3>\n				<p>There are various documents and requirements needed before you able to register. Read our list for everything you require\n</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/documents/\" role=\"button\">\n						Documents & Prerequisites\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-1024x683.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-300x200.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-768x512.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-640x427.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-400x267.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-367x245.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					Register through the MoC <br><br>\nwebsite\n				</h3>\n				<p>Once you have all the documents, you are now ready to register through the Ministry of Commerce website. There are three steps; register as a new user, reserve a name, then proceed to fill out the online form</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/elementor-746-3/\" role=\"button\">\n						Learn more\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"570\" height=\"329\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22.jpg 570w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-300x173.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-400x231.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-367x212.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					File Annual Declaration\n				</h3>\n				<p>The Ministry of Commerce registration process is nearly completed, the last step is to file for the annual declaration</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/annual-declaration/\" role=\"button\">\n						Learn more\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"570\" height=\"329\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23.jpg 570w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23-300x173.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23-400x231.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23-367x212.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" />											\n			<h2><a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Registering-a-Business-Checklist.pdf\">Download our Checklist Here</a></h2>		\n			<h5>Our detailed, Printable checklist will help you simplify the registration process</h5>		\n			<h2>General Department of Tax</h2>		\n				<h3>\n					Collect all the documents <br><br>\nand prerequisites\n				</h3>\n				<p>There are various documents and requirements needed to register at the General Department of Tax, many of which are the same for the MoC. Read our list for everything you require\n</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/documents-2/\" role=\"button\">\n						Documents & Prerequisites\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-1024x683.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-300x200.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-768x512.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-640x427.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-400x267.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-367x245.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					Register at the National Tax <br><br>\nSchool\n				</h3>\n				<p>The GDT does not have an online registration process at the moment so you are required to go to the National Tax School in person</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/elementor-746-2-2/\" role=\"button\">\n						Read more\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"570\" height=\"329\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22.jpg 570w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-300x173.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-400x231.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-367x212.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" />											\n			<h2>NEED HELP?</h2>		\n			<p>Our team at Ngeay Ngeay can take care of all your registration needs</p>		\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/contact-us/\" role=\"button\">\n						Contact Us\n					</a>', 'Registering a Business Checklist good', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '998-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 17:42:51', '2019-06-22 10:42:51', '', '998', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/998-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1327', '1', '2019-06-22 17:43:49', '2019-06-22 10:43:49', '<h2>Registering a Business</h2>		\n		<p>What you need to know to register a business in Cambodia</p>		\n			<h2>Ministry of Commerce</h2>		\n				<h3>\n					Know your Business Status\n				</h3>\n				<p>There are a variety of business statuses in Cambodia, the most common are sole proprietor, partnership and limited liability companies. Read our article for more information</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/business-status/\" role=\"button\">\n						Read more here\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-1024x683.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-300x200.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-768x512.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-640x427.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-400x267.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-367x245.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					Collect all the documents <br><br>\nand prerequisites\n				</h3>\n				<p>There are various documents and requirements needed before you able to register. Read our list for everything you require\n</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/documents/\" role=\"button\">\n						Documents & Prerequisites\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-1024x683.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-300x200.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-768x512.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-640x427.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-400x267.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-367x245.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					Register through the MoC <br><br>\nwebsite\n				</h3>\n				<p>Once you have all the documents, you are now ready to register through the Ministry of Commerce website. There are three steps; register as a new user, reserve a name, then proceed to fill out the online form</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/elementor-746-3/\" role=\"button\">\n						Learn more\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"570\" height=\"329\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22.jpg 570w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-300x173.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-400x231.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-367x212.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					File Annual Declaration\n				</h3>\n				<p>The Ministry of Commerce registration process is nearly completed, the last step is to file for the annual declaration</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/annual-declaration/\" role=\"button\">\n						Learn more\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"570\" height=\"329\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23.jpg 570w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23-300x173.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23-400x231.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23-367x212.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" />											\n			<h2><a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Registering-a-Business-Checklist.pdf\">Download our Checklist Here</a></h2>		\n			<h5>Our detailed, Printable checklist will help you simplify the registration process</h5>		\n			<h2>General Department of Tax</h2>		\n				<h3>\n					Collect all the documents <br><br>\nand prerequisites\n				</h3>\n				<p>There are various documents and requirements needed to register at the General Department of Tax, many of which are the same for the MoC. Read our list for everything you require\n</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/documents-2/\" role=\"button\">\n						Documents & Prerequisites\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-1024x683.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-300x200.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-768x512.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-640x427.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-400x267.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-367x245.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					Register at the National Tax <br><br>\nSchool\n				</h3>\n				<p>The GDT does not have an online registration process at the moment so you are required to go to the National Tax School in person</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/elementor-746-2-2/\" role=\"button\">\n						Read more\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"570\" height=\"329\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22.jpg 570w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-300x173.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-400x231.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-367x212.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" />											\n			<h2>NEED HELP?</h2>		\n			<p>Our team at Ngeay Ngeay can take care of all your registration needs</p>		\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/contact-us/\" role=\"button\">\n						Contact Us\n					</a>', 'Registering a Business Checklist good - G', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '998-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 17:43:49', '2019-06-22 10:43:49', '', '998', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/998-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1328', '1', '2019-06-22 17:44:58', '2019-06-22 10:44:58', '<h2>Salaries &amp; Compensation</h2>		\n		<p>Everything you need to know about salaries and compensation in Cambodia</p>		\n		<p><strong>Fortnightly Payments</strong></p><p>As of January 1<sup>st</sup>, 2019, all businesses are required to pay their employees two times per month. The first payment shall be 50% of the employees’ net wage and the second payment shall contain the remaining net wages plus any benefits owed.</p><p><strong>Minimum Wage</strong></p><p>There is no official minimum wage in Cambodia, however the general consensus is that the minimum wage should be set at the Garment Industry minimum wage which is $182/month for a 48-hour week.</p><p><strong>Overtime</strong></p><p>Overtime is classified as any hours above the normal working hours, which at a minimum must be no more than 9 hours/day, and no more than 48 hours per week. Any hours worked above these hours or the hours agreed upon employment are deemed to be overtime.</p><p>Overtime must be paid at 150% of wages or 200% of wages if worked between 10pm and 5am.</p><p>Additionally, workers may be entitled to days in lieu, if they are need to work on a typical rest day, the employees are entitled to take another day off.</p><p><strong>Public Holidays</strong></p><p>All employees are entitled to public holiday leave according the public holiday sub-decree issued by the government. In the case a public holiday is on a Sunday, employees are entitled to take the following Monday off work.</p><p>If businesses are required to open on public holidays, employees can work voluntarily but are entitled to pay of 200% of their normal wage.</p>', 'Salaries & Compensation - G', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1196-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-22 17:44:58', '2019-06-22 10:44:58', '', '1196', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/22/1196-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
