INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1381', '1', '2019-06-23 11:13:18', '2019-06-23 04:13:18', '<h2>Annual Taxes</h2>		\n		<p>Every year on the 31st of March annual taxes need to be filed for every business. This is quite a complex process and we recommend hiring a professional firm to assist</p>		\n		<p><strong>Annual tax on profit</strong></p><p>At the end of the year, you will have to pay a tax for a total amount of 20% of your profit. You can then deduce the 1% you paid every month during the year.<br /><br /></p><p>Annual taxable profit in USD for a limited company:<br />&lt; 1,463 USD                     0%<br />1,463 – 3,658 USD          5%<br />3,658 – 24,878 USD       10%<br />24,878 – 36,585 USD     15%<br />&gt; 36,585 USD                   20%</p><p> </p><p><strong>Small Taxpayers</strong></p><p>The patent tax for sole proprietorships and partnerships is $100, which is approx. KHR400,000.</p><p><strong>Medium &amp; Large Taxpayers</strong></p><p>The patent tax is a fixed annual fee. It depends on which taxpayer category your company belongs to (small, medium or large). These are the official patent tax amounts:</p><p>Medium Taxpayer          KHR1,200,000/USD300</p><p>Large Taxpayer             KHR3,000,000 or KHR5,000,000*/ USD750 or USD1,250</p><p>*If the annual turnover of the Large Taxpayer exceeds KHR10,000 million (USD2.5 million) then the Patent Tax payable will be USD1,250.</p><p>If the annual turnover of the Large Taxpayer is less than KHR10,000 million (USD2.5 million) the Patent Tax payable will be USD750.</p>', 'Annual Taxes-G', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1186-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-23 11:13:18', '2019-06-23 04:13:18', '', '1186', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/23/1186-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1383', '1', '2019-06-23 11:22:42', '2019-06-23 04:22:42', '<h2>Contracts</h2>		\n		<p>There are two types of contracts in Cambodian Labor Law, fixed duration contracts (FDC’s) and Unfixed Duration Contracts (UDC’s).</p>		\n		<p><strong>Fixed Duration Contracts</strong></p><p>These contracts are for a fixed term, and can be anywhere up to 2 years in length. After two years the employer can decide to renew the contract or not renew the contract. A fixed term contract must be in writing.</p><p>If the contract finishes, and the employee continues working without a contract, the employee is understood to be on a UDC</p><p>If a fixed term contract expires or is terminated, the employee has the right to severance pay of 5% of total wages over the contract (Article 73). If a FDC is terminated early, the employer is required to payout the entire the value of the contract.</p><p><strong>Unfixed Duration Contracts</strong></p><p>Unfixed duration contracts are for an unspecified amount of time and can be either verbal or written.</p><p>For terminating a UDC  the minimum period of notice is:</p><ul><li>Seven days, if the worker\'s length of continuous service is less than six months;</li><li>Fifteen days, if the worker\'s length of continuous service is from six months to two years;</li><li>One month, if the worker\'s length of continuous service is longer than two years and up to five years.</li><li>Two months, if the worker\'s length of continuous service is longer than five years and up to ten years.</li><li>Three months, if the worker\'s length of continuous service is longer than then years.</li></ul><p>Seniority payments are also applicable to UDC’s. For more information please see the Seniority Payments section</p>', 'Contracts - G', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1153-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-23 11:22:42', '2019-06-23 04:22:42', '', '1153', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/23/1153-revision-v1/', '0', 