 time management means less time working as you are able to achieve more in less time, this means you are able to switch off and spend more time playing sport, relaxing and spending time with the people most important to you.\n\nListen to Sreypov talk about how improving her time management has helped her business.\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DPu1n3g1dr0&amp;t=69s', 'Importance of Time Management', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1404-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-23 15:05:07', '2019-06-23 08:05:07', '', '1404', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/23/1404-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1409', '1', '2019-06-23 15:08:52', '2019-06-23 08:08:52', '<h2>Basic Business Financial Management</h2>		\n		<p>Financial management is a crucial task for any business owner, whether you own a small stall on the side of a road or a large company. For small business owners, it is often very difficult to know where to start or how to manage your finances.</p>		\n		<p>It is important for small and inexperienced business owners to keep it as simple as possible in the beginning. The first step to managing your finances is tracking your finances, tracking your finances means recording all the money that comes into your business, all the money that goes out of your business and where possible to count your inventory.</p><p><strong>Sales Day Book</strong></p><p>The sales day book is the spreadsheet or book that you record all the money that comes into your business through sales. For each purchase that a customer makes, you need to record</p><ul><li>the date</li><li>the items</li><li>how much you received for the items.</li></ul><p>At the end of each day, record the total amount of money that came into your business. See our template here.</p><p><strong>Purchases Day Book</strong></p><p>The purchases day book is the spreadsheet or book that you record all the money that goes out of your business through purchases (expenses). For each expense that you pay for, you need to record</p><ul><li>the date</li><li>the items</li><li>how much you received for the items.</li></ul><p>At the end of each day, record the total amount of money that you spent, See our template here.</p><p>At the end of each day, from the amount of money you had at the start of the day, add the total of the sales day book and minus the purchases day book, this will equal the total amount of money you have, check to see if its correct.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Inventory Day Book</strong></p><p>The inventory day book is the spreadsheet or book that you record how much inventory you have, depending on how much inventory you have, you can do this each day, each week or each month. See our template here.</p><p>Watch the video of Sreypov to see how understanding your business finances can help you grow your business.</p>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lcfWjsa5RLg', 'Basic Business Financial Management', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'elementor-1404-2', '', '', '2019-06-24 10:28:50', '2019-06-24 03:28:50', '', '0', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/?p=1409', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1411', '1', '2019-06-23 15:41:42', '2019-06-23 08:41:42', '<h2>Start with WHY</h2>\nCreating a team of loyal followers and a company with loyal customers is incredibly difficult and there are not many leaders or companies that have really achieved this\n\nCompanies like Apple, Harley Davidson or Brown Coffee, have started something special with incredibly loyal customers, followers and teams.\n\nThese companies and leaders are able to inspire their employees to go through all the hard times with them and come out the other end, how do these companies and leaders achieve this? Money? Benefits? Extra Holidays? These are nice, but they do not inspire loyalty, when they can no longer get more money or more benefits, employees will leave. So how do they do it? These companies and leaders start with WHY.\n\nIn Simon Sinek’s now famous TED talk, he talks about a three layer circle, WHY being at the center, how in the next ring, and what in the outer circle.\n\n<img width=\"408\" height=\"343\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WHY.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WHY.png 408w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WHY-300x252.png 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WHY-400x336.png 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WHY-367x309.png 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 408px) 100vw, 408px\">\n\nMost companies and leaders can answer the WHAT, this is easy, describing your products and industry, some leaders can answer the HOW, your value proposition, unique selling point and add ons. But the WHY? The reason the company exists, WHY is the company doing this? WHY should anyone (staff, customers, beneficiaries) care?\n\nAt Ngeay Ngeay, we will often ask business owners to describe their core focus in two parts:\n\nOne sentence on their niche, or really what we’re asking is the WHAT &amp; HOW, every business owner we’ve worked with is able to tell us this easily. The second part is harder, we ask them, what is the businesses (or the leaders) passion, or cause, or purpose. This is the WHY, 90% of the businesses we work with have a lot of trouble answering this.\n\nSinek, says that most companies will start with the WHAT, then move on to the HOW and sometimes they get to WHY, but great companies will start with WHY as this provides all the reason WHY anyone should follow them, staff or customers. With this in the mind, the WHAT is the proof that belief.\n\nCan you clearly articulate the WHY of your business? Do your staff now your WHY?\n\nIf you need help providing direction for your business, our team can help\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7zFeuSagktM', 'Start with WHY', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'elementor-1404-3', '', '', '2019-07-23 10:50:47', '2019-07-23 03:50:47', '', '0', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/?p=1411', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1415', '1', '2019-06-23 15:12:40', '2019-06-23 08:12:40', '<h2>The Importance of Time Management</h2>\nTime is one of the most valuable assets we have, and everyone has the same amount, whether you are a millionaire or an executive of a large corporation you still only have 24 hours a day just like everybody.&nbsp;\n\nThis means that if you can utilise your time better you have an automatic advantage over other people and can achieve more, be more relaxed and be able to spend more time with the people most important to you.\n\nTo be able to be better at time management it is important to understand why it is so valuable. Here are 3 reasons why time management is crucial to your success and well-being:\n<ol>\n 	<li>Better results with less effort</li>\n</ol>\nWhen you really master time management, you improve your ability to focusing on a task. When you can really focus on a task and not get distracted with Facebook, emails, chats, or other distractions you can achieve an astonishing amount of work in a short amount of time. The result? Improved results, with much less effort.\n<ol start=\"2\">\n 	<li>Better Decision making</li>\n</ol>\nWhen you are able to manage your time effectively, your stress levels are reduced significantly. No more thinking, I need to this… I need to do that…. With great time management, you know what needs to be done and know how to focus on getting it done. Without getting too technical, no matter how logical we think our decisions are, every decision we make has an emotional component to it. When we have less stress, we are able to make clearer decisions as our emotions are more stable. For more information about decision making and emotions you can read Thinking Fast and Slow by Daniel Kahneman.\n<ol start=\"3\">\n 	<li>More time with family &amp; friends</li>\n</ol>\nLastly, with better time management you are able to spend more time with your family and friends and doing activities that you enjoy. Better time management means less time working as you are able to achieve more in less time, this means you are able to switch off and spend more time playing sport, relaxing and spending time with the people most important to you.\n\nListen to Sreypov talk about how improving her time management has helped her business.\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DPu1n3g1dr0&amp;t=69s', 'Importance of Time Management', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1409-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-23 15:12:40', '2019-06-23 08:12:40', '', '1409', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/23/1409-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1416', '1', '2019-06-23 15:12:41', '2019-06-23 08:12:41', '<h2>Basic Business Financial Management</h2>		\n		<p>Financial management is a crucial task for any business owner, whether you own a small stall on the side of a road or a large company. For small business owners, it is often very difficult to know where to start or how to manage your finances.</p>		\n		<p>It is important for small and inexperienced business owners to keep it as simple as possible in the beginning. The first step to managing your finances is tracking your finances, tracking your finances means recording all the money that comes into your business, all the money that goes out of your business and where possible to count your inventory.</p><p><strong>Sales Day Book</strong></p><p>The sales day book is the spreadsheet or book that you record all the money that comes into your business through sales. For each purchase that a customer makes, you need to record</p><ul><li>the date</li><li>the items</li><li>how much you received for the items.</li></ul><p>At the end of each day, record the total amount of money that came into your business. See our template here.</p><p><strong>Purchases Day Book</strong></p><p>The purchases day book is the spreadsheet or book that you record all the money that goes out of your business through purchases (expenses). For each expense that you pay for, you need to record</p><ul><li>the date</li><li>the items</li><li>how much you received for the items.</li></ul><p>At the end of each day, record the total amount of money that you spent, See our template here.</p><p>At the end of each day, from the amount of money you had at the start of the day, add the total of the sales day book and minus the purchases day book, this will equal the total amount of money you have, check to see if its correct.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Inventory Day Book</strong></p><p>The inventory day book is the spreadsheet or book that you record how much inventory you have, depending on how much inventory you have, you can do this each day, each week or each month. See our template here.</p><p>Watch the video of Sreypov to see how understanding your business finances can help you grow your business.</p>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lcfWjsa5RLg', 'Importance of Time Management', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1409-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-23 15:12:41', '2019-06-23 08:12:41', '', '1409', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/23/1409-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1417', '1', '2019-06-23 15:13:16', '2019-06-23 08:13:16', '<h2>Basic Business Financial Management</h2>\nFinancial management is a crucial task for any business owner, whether you own a small stall on the side of a road or a large company. For small business owners, it is often very difficult to know where to start or how to manage your finances.\n\nIt is important for small and inexperienced business owners to keep it as simple as possible in the beginning. The first step to managing your finances is tracking your finances, tracking your finances means recording all the money that comes into your business, all the money that goes out of your business and where possible to count your inventory.\n\n<strong>Sales Day Book</strong>\n\nThe sales day book is the spreadsheet or book that you record all the money that comes into your business through sales. For each purchase that a customer makes, you need to record\n<ul>\n 	<li>the date</li>\n 	<li>the items</li>\n 	<li>how much you received for the items.</li>\n</ul>\nAt the end of each day, record the total amount of money that came into your business. See our template here.\n\n<strong>Purchases Day Book</strong>\n\nThe purchases day book is the spreadsheet or book that you record all the money that goes out of your business through purchases (expenses). For each expense that you pay for, you need to record\n<ul>\n 	<li>the date</li>\n 	<li>the items</li>\n 	<li>how much you received for the items.</li>\n</ul>\nAt the end of each day, record the total amount of money that you spent, See our template here.\n\nAt the end of each day, from the amount of money you had at the start of the day, add the total of the sales day book and minus the purchases day book, this will equal the total amount of money you have, check to see if its correct.\n\n<strong>Inventory Day Book</strong>\n\nThe inventory day book is the spreadsheet or book that you record how much inventory you have, depending on how much inventory you have, you can do this each day, each week or each month. See our template here.\n\nWatch the video of Sreypov to see how understanding your business finances can help you grow your business.\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lcfWjsa5RLg', 'Basic Business Financial Management', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1409-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-23 15:13:16', '2019-06-23 08:13:16', '', '1409', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/23/1409-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
