INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1435', '1', '2019-06-24 10:28:50', '2019-06-24 03:28:50', '<h2>Basic Business Financial Management</h2>		\n		<p>Financial management is a crucial task for any business owner, whether you own a small stall on the side of a road or a large company. For small business owners, it is often very difficult to know where to start or how to manage your finances.</p>		\n		<p>It is important for small and inexperienced business owners to keep it as simple as possible in the beginning. The first step to managing your finances is tracking your finances, tracking your finances means recording all the money that comes into your business, all the money that goes out of your business and where possible to count your inventory.</p><p><strong>Sales Day Book</strong></p><p>The sales day book is the spreadsheet or book that you record all the money that comes into your business through sales. For each purchase that a customer makes, you need to record</p><ul><li>the date</li><li>the items</li><li>how much you received for the items.</li></ul><p>At the end of each day, record the total amount of money that came into your business. See our template here.</p><p><strong>Purchases Day Book</strong></p><p>The purchases day book is the spreadsheet or book that you record all the money that goes out of your business through purchases (expenses). For each expense that you pay for, you need to record</p><ul><li>the date</li><li>the items</li><li>how much you received for the items.</li></ul><p>At the end of each day, record the total amount of money that you spent, See our template here.</p><p>At the end of each day, from the amount of money you had at the start of the day, add the total of the sales day book and minus the purchases day book, this will equal the total amount of money you have, check to see if its correct.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Inventory Day Book</strong></p><p>The inventory day book is the spreadsheet or book that you record how much inventory you have, depending on how much inventory you have, you can do this each day, each week or each month. See our template here.</p><p>Watch the video of Sreypov to see how understanding your business finances can help you grow your business.</p>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lcfWjsa5RLg', 'Basic Business Financial Management', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1409-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-24 10:28:50', '2019-06-24 03:28:50', '', '1409', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/06/24/1409-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
