INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1826', '1', '2019-07-23 11:09:46', '2019-07-23 04:09:46', '<h2>Filling the annual declaration</h2>		\n		<p>Each year you have to file an annual declaration to the Ministry of Commerce</p>		\n		<p>When you register your business and each year after, all limited liability companies will have to file an annual declaration through the Ministry of Commerce’s registration website.  </p><p>Within 1 month from your registration, you will get informed by email to update your annual declaration.  If you forget to do this, you may receive a fine. You will need to have registered for tax before you can file the annual declaration as you will need your tax registration number (TIN). </p><p><strong>Step 1</strong> : Search for your company in the database (with the company’s name or company number) and click on it.</p><p><strong>Step 2</strong>: Log in with the account for the registration</p><p><strong>Step 3</strong>: File the annual declaration. The information you will need: company addresses, director details, shareholdings, and annual return reminder details. You also need your TIN (Tax Identification Number) and Tax registration date.</p><p><strong>Step 4</strong>: Pay the annual fee online if you have the ACLEDA bank, if you do not have an ACLEDA bank you will have to go to ACLEDA bank and send your receipt to the Ministry of Commerce</p><p><em><strong>Cost</strong> : 80000 Riels/USD 20</em></p><p> </p>', 'Filing annual declaration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '874-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:09:46', '2019-07-23 04:09:46', '', '874', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/874-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1828', '1', '2019-07-23 11:09:53', '2019-07-23 04:09:53', '<h2>Filling out the online form</h2>		\n		<p>The online form for business registration is a complex form and requires you to upload various documents including your Memorandum and Articles of Association</p>		\n		<p>Note that from the moment you start your application, you have 15 days to complete it, otherwise you will need to begin the application process again.</p><p>If you want to register a limited company (private/public) or a foreign company.</p><p>Choose “Companies” and then “Incorporate a Private Limited Company/Incorporate a Public Limited Company” in the left menu. You will have to fill in the following sections.</p><p><strong>Step 1: Your business</strong></p><p><em>General details</em></p><ul><li>Check the box “select a reserve name” and then chose the name of the company (that you already reserved) in the “drop-down bar”.</li><li>Upload your memorandum and articles of association</li></ul><p><em>Business activities</em></p><ul><li>Define your business objective. This is the general activity of your company. Business objectives are associated with codes and proposed in the drop-down bar. You just have to pick the one which fits best with your company objective.</li><li>Define your main business activities. They are more precise than the business objective and again choose the one that is most appropriate in the drop-down bar.</li><li>Write your share par value in both USD and riel. This will be in your Memorandum &amp; Articles of Association</li><li>Provide the number of male and female employees and the number of Cambodian employees and number of foreign employees</li><li>“Employee position details” have to be uploaded. Please refer to our template and fill it with the information about your staff</li><li>Any supporting documents that you think may be appropriate can also be uploaded</li></ul><p><strong>Step 2: Addresses</strong></p><ul><li>Fill the details of your office address and upload your proof of location on the same page (property tax receipt)</li><li>Tick the box if the postal address is the same as your office address.</li><li>Provide your email address and your phone number.</li><li style=\"list-style-type: none;\"> </li><li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">Below is a video from the Ministry of Commerce explaining how to use the online system</li></ul>https://youtu.be/sqHEAWH8lOghttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3BaFbTghCW4<p><strong>Step 3: Directors</strong></p><ul><li>If you are one of the directors, you can push the “add me as a director” button, then your information will be automatically filled for the page. If you are not one of the directors, then you should manually fill the information of the directors.</li><li>Chose the proof of identity you want to use (passport or ID) and give its details. Then upload the proof of ID you already scanned.</li><li>Tick the box if you are the chairman of the Board of Directors. The chairman means the most senior person in the business.</li><li>Tick the “consent box” that insures you have not been convicted for any crime and that all the information you provided is true.</li><li>Upload the director consent. This letter proves you have no criminal background signed by the director of your company (see our template on this link)</li><li>Then you can add another director’s details if there is another one.</li></ul><p><strong>Step 4: Shares &amp; shareholders</strong></p><ul><li>“More than one class of share” Yes/no. For most companies, this will be no, if you are unsure, then select no</li><li>Select in the drop-down bar if the shareholder is an individual</li><li>If one of the directors you gave information about are part of the shareholders, then tick the box “select from the list of directors” and select him/her. The information you already filled will be automatically saved. You can also add yourself as a shareholder, by pushing the corresponding button</li><li>If shareholders are not directors or yourself, please fill in the information. You can also add another shareholder by pushing the button at the end. Every time you add a shareholder, it is asked how many shares each of them owns and you will need to upload their proof of ID.</li><li>After you have added every shareholder, select the nationality of the majority shareholders, as well as the percentage of the majority shareholders.</li></ul><p><strong>Step 5: Review the information</strong></p><p>You have now filled all the necessary information for your application, you will need to review the information and be sure that it is all correct and all required documents are uploaded. Click on the icon buttons at the top to modify.</p><p><strong>DO NOT SUBMIT YOUR APPLICATION YET.</strong></p><p>If you HAVE an ACLEDA bank account…</p><p>Click on “submit” to confirm your application, you will get access to ACLEDA pop-up page and you can make your payment. </p><p>If you do not have an ACLEDA account, you will need to go pay at ACLEDA in person and take your receipt to the Department of Accounting and Finance at the MoC. You have 15 days to complete this. </p>		\n							Previous\n							Next', 'Filling out the online form', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '853-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:09:53', '2019-07-23 04:09:53', '', '853', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/853-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1830', '1', '2019-07-23 11:10:11', '2019-07-23 04:10:11', '<h2>How to find capital?</h2>		\n		<p>At Ngeay Ngeay, this is is one of the most commonly asked questions we receive, “How can I get funding?”, “Where can I get capital?”</p>		\n		<p><strong>How can I get funding?</strong></p><p>When entrepreneurs or small business owners ask us this, the first thing we ask back, is “What do you need funding for?” Often the answer is for the operations of the business, which to us means that they do not need external funding, but better cashflow management. There are only a few genuine reasons to need external funding,</p><ul><li>you need capital to grow and you have a plan on how you are going to do this (eg. New shop, building a factory, expanding operations)</li><li>you need an expensive piece of equipment</li><li>in rare cases for emergency cashflow (but you need to seek proper financial advice).</li></ul><p>If you are not in any of these positions, but you feel you need funding, we recommend you read our information on cashflow management here.</p><p>If you are looking to grow, or you need equipment then you have a few options on where you can get funding.</p><p><strong>1. Personal Funds &amp; Family &amp; Friends</strong></p><p>This is often the best option, if it is available, the reason is it less risky, if the business fails, you will not owe the banks or money lenders money. You can receive investment from family and friends, which can often be done at lower interest rates and family and friends will require less paperwork. However, you need to be sure that your family or friends understand the risk they are taking on and that investing in a small business is risky. Additionally, be clear about the terms of the loan or investment and make sure it is written down.</p><p><strong>2. Microfinance Institutions (MFI)</strong></p><p>Depending on how much money you need and what you need it for, often the next easiest option for funding is from MFI’s, however, you will often need some collateral for these loans and they have large interest rates, and many times will have hidden fees. See our article here on what to look for before you receive a loan.</p><p><strong>3. Banks</strong></p><p>Similar to MFI’s, banks are a good choice for loans, however in our experience, it is more difficult to receive a loan from a bank. You will need some collateral, normally in the form of land, to secure your loan. The interest rates for bank loans are generally better than MFI’s but as mentioned much harder to receive.</p><p><strong>4. Grants</strong></p><p>There are many grants in Cambodia for small businesses, particularly if your business can show that it benefits society in some way. Grants are usually funded by large NGO’s, governments, or foundations, most grants will have an application form that you will need to explain about your business, and what you will do the money. See <a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/funding-opportunities/\">Funding Opportunities</a> for updates on grants that come out.</p>', 'Finding Capital', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1057-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:10:11', '2019-07-23 04:10:11', '', '1057', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/1057-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1832', '1', '2019-07-23 11:10:21', '2019-07-23 04:10:21', '<h2>FUNDING OPPORTUNITIES</h2>		\n			<h3>GRANTS, LOANS &amp; Investments</h3>		\n		<p>Here are some current grant opportunities that may apply to your business</p>		\n										<img width=\"85\" height=\"85\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-1-2-85x85.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-1-2-85x85.png 85w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-1-2-150x150.png 150w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-1-2-300x300.png 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-1-2-768x768.png 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-1-2-640x640.png 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-1-2-400x400.png 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-1-2-560x560.png 560w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-1-2-367x367.png 367w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-1-2-50x50.png 50w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1-1-2.png 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 85px) 100vw, 85px\" />											\n			<h3>Thriive Cambodia</h3>		\n		<p>Thriive provides pay-it-forward loans , up to $10,000 in value for equipment </p>		\n			<h5>Contact Thriive</h5>		\n										<img width=\"85\" height=\"85\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/pact-85x85.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/pact-85x85.png 85w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/pact-150x150.png 150w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/pact-50x50.png 50w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 85px) 100vw, 85px\" />											\n			<h3>Pact Cambodia</h3>		\n		<p>Through the We Act project Pact Cambodia have various proposals available </p>		\n			<h5>Find out more</h5>		\n										<img width=\"85\" height=\"85\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/ppcbank-85x85.jpeg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/ppcbank-85x85.jpeg 85w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/ppcbank-150x150.jpeg 150w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/ppcbank-50x50.jpeg 50w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/ppcbank.jpeg 200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 85px) 100vw, 85px\" />											\n			<h3>PPCBank</h3>		\n		<p>Launching soon, PPCBank have announced a new SME lending product</p>		\n			<h5>Read More</h5>		\n										<img width=\"157\" height=\"50\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Dev-Innovations-logo-temp-5.png\" alt=\"\" />											\n			<h3>Development Innovations</h3>		\n		<p>Development Innovations has a great funding tracker on their website</p>		\n			<h5>Read More</h5>		\n										<img width=\"85\" height=\"85\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bredbank-85x85.jpeg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bredbank-85x85.jpeg 85w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bredbank-150x150.jpeg 150w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bredbank-50x50.jpeg 50w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bredbank.jpeg 225w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 85px) 100vw, 85px\" />											\n			<h3>Bred Bank</h3>		\n		<p>Launching soon, Bred Bank ahve announced a product for female led SME\'s</p>		\n			<h5>FIND out More</h5>		\n										<img width=\"64\" height=\"64\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1465236987_resolutions-16.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1465236987_resolutions-16.png 64w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/1465236987_resolutions-16-50x50.png 50w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 64px) 100vw, 64px\" />											\n			<h3>CONTACT US</h3>		\n		<p>If you would like your funding opportunity to be listed here, contact us below</p>		\n			<h5>Contact us</h5>', 'Funding Opportunities', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '877-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:10:21', '2019-07-23 04:10:21', '', '877', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/877-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1834', '1', '2019-07-23 11:10:29', '2019-07-23 04:10:29', '<h2>How to find Start Up Capital</h2>		\n		<p>When we talk to budding entrepreneurs, one of the most common questions we get asked is how can I start a business if I don\'t have any money. Below you will find the most common ways to get startup capital for a new business</p>		\n		<p><strong>Using your own resources</strong></p><p>Many businesses do not need a lot of start up capital, and often your dream business can be scaled down so that you can begin with little money and build your way up. This is also a very good way of testing your target market, and your value proposition. Think about how you can save your money to start a very small business, and use the profits of that to save more to build a bigger business. Often many entrepreneurs in the beginning will have multipe jobs, they will have their normal job as well as run their business until they have enough capital to do their business 100%.</p><p><strong>Family and Friends</strong></p><p>Asking family and friend for money is one of the most common ways entrepreneurs can get started. Again, this will often mean that you have to start a smaller scale business until you can generate enough funds to start a bigger business, but this is a great way to start. </p><p><strong>Grants</strong></p><p>There are many grants that will help fund small businesses, if you have a unique idea then you can look at the many grants that come up in Cambodia to see if your idea fits with those.</p><p><strong>Micro-loans</strong></p><p>Micro-loans are some of the easiest loans to receive in Cambodia and this can be a great way to get started. You need to be very aware of the costs involved and watch out for any hidden costs. See our loan calculator to help you see how much you will pay in interest.</p><p><strong>Investment and Loans</strong></p><p>It is often very difficult to get investment and larger loans for a non-existing business, however it does happen occasionally. If you would like to talk further about investment please contact us at ngeayngeay.co and we can help direct you to investors.</p><p>See our <a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/funding-opportunities/\">Funding Opportunities</a> page for upcoming opportunities for your business</p><p> </p>', 'How to find startup capital', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1295-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:10:29', '2019-07-23 04:10:29', '', '1295', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/1295-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1836', '1', '2019-07-23 11:10:37', '2019-07-23 04:10:37', '<h2>Leave</h2>		\n		<p>There are various types of leave that employees are obligated to receive in Cambodia</p>		\n		<p><strong>Annual Leave</strong></p><p>Annual leave is provided to all employees once they have completed 1 year of service. Annual leave is on a pro-rata rate, of 18 days after 1 years service, based on a 48 hour work week. If the employee works less than 48 hours, for example, 40 hours, then the employee is provided 15 days of annual leave.</p><p>For every 3 years of service the employee is entitled to an extra day of annual leave per year.</p><p><strong>Weekly Rest</strong></p><p>All employees are entitled to 24 consecutive hours of rest per week</p><p><strong>Sick Leave</strong></p><p>The labour law requires a business to provide a sick leave to employees, if they have a letter from a certified doctor for up to 6 months, after 6 months the business can terminate the employee. The rates of pay for the employee during the sick period is as follows:</p><ul><li>During the 1st month of illness: 100% of wages,</li><li>During the 2nd and 3rd months of illness: 60% of wages,</li><li>During the 4th month and longer: no wages paid</li></ul><p><strong>Maternity Leave</strong></p><p>All women are entitled to maternity leave of 90 days, the employee is entitled to half the wages and benefits.</p><p><strong>Public Holidays</strong></p><p>All employees are entitled to public holiday leave according the public holiday sub-decree issued by the government. In the case a public holiday is on a Sunday, employees are entitled to take the following Monday off work.</p><p>If businesses are required to open on public holidays, employees can work voluntarily but are entitled to pay of 200% of their normal wage.</p>', 'Leave', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1176-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:10:37', '2019-07-23 04:10:37', '', '1176', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/1176-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1838', '1', '2019-07-23 11:10:44', '2019-07-23 04:10:44', '<h2>Ministry of Labour Registration</h2>		\n		<p>All business registered with the MoC and General Department of Tax need to be registered with the Ministry of Labour.</p>		\n		<p>To register at the Ministry of Labour you will need</p><ul><li>Tax Patent</li><li>Certificate of Incorporation</li><li>Employee List (see template here)</li><li>Ministry of Labour forms filled out</li></ul><p>Take all the documents to the building called “General Labour” or អគ្គការងារ, on level 3. The general Labour building is at the back on the right.</p><p> </p>		\n			<iframe frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?q=ministry%20of%20labour&amp;t=m&amp;z=14&amp;output=embed&amp;iwloc=near\" aria-label=\"ministry of labour\"></iframe>', 'Ministry of Labour Registration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1180-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:10:44', '2019-07-23 04:10:44', '', '1180', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/1180-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1840', '1', '2019-07-23 11:10:59', '2019-07-23 04:10:59', '<h2>Monthly Taxes &amp; Obligations</h2>		\n		<p>Everything you need to know to be compliant with the Cambodian Law</p>		\n				<h3>\n					Required Accounting\n				</h3>\n				<p>Here is a brief overview of the required accounting for the various business statuses</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/required-accounting/\" role=\"button\">\n						Read more here\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0832-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0832-1024x683.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0832-300x200.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0832-768x512.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0832-640x427.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0832-400x267.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0832-367x245.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					Monthly Taxes\n				</h3>\n				<p>Here is a brief overview of how to file your monthly taxes including links to the online forms</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/monthly-taxes/\" role=\"button\">\n						Read more here\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0745-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0745-1024x683.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0745-300x200.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0745-768x512.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0745-640x427.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0745-400x267.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0745-367x245.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					E-VAT\n				</h3>\n				<p>Here is a brief overview of how to use the newly released E-VAT system</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/e-vat/\" role=\"button\">\n						Read more here\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"618\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0307-1024x618.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0307-1024x618.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0307-300x181.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0307-768x463.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0307-640x386.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0307-400x241.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0307-367x221.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n			<h2>NEED HELP?</h2>		\n			<p>Our partners can help provide you with your monthly tax need</p>		\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/contact-us/\" role=\"button\">\n						See HERE\n					</a>', 'Monthly Taxes & Obligations', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1159-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:10:59', '2019-07-23 04:10:59', '', '1159', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/1159-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1842', '1', '2019-07-23 11:11:08', '2019-07-23 04:11:08', '<h2>Monthly Taxes</h2>		\n		<p>Filing monthly taxes is a complex process for medium and large taxpayers. We highly recommend you hire a professional to assist you</p>		\n		<p>Each month you will have to pay your taxes, this includes your value added tax (VAT), tax on salary, minimum tax on profit, withholding tax and public lighting tax. Additionally you will need to pay your NSSF fees (see here).</p><p>Filing and payment of taxes in Cambodia for medium and large taxpayers is quite complex, we highly recommend that you hire a professional to assist you in this process. However, it is important you understand the basic process, as its your responsibility to ensure that all the taxes are paid correctly.</p><p>For small taxpayers (sole proprietors and partnerships), you only need to fill out one form. The instructions are found on the second page of the form.</p><p>For medium and large taxpayers, there are multiple forms and evidence that is required.</p><p>To file your taxes you need to download the appropriate forms found here. You will need to fill out all the forms and provide the necessary evidence, you need to hand these forms in, with payment to your local tax department for your Khan. Monthly taxes are due on the 20<sup>th</sup> of each month.</p><p><a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/tax-nssf-rates/\">For the latest tax rates, see here.</a></p>', 'Monthly Taxes', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1156-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:11:08', '2019-07-23 04:11:08', '', '1156', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/1156-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1844', '1', '2019-07-23 11:11:18', '2019-07-23 04:11:18', '<h2>NSSF Registration</h2>		\n		<p>After registration with the Ministry of Labour, you will need to register with the NSSF</p>		\n		<p>For the NSSF registration you will need</p><ul><li>Tax patent</li><li>Certificate of Incorporation</li><li>Employee list</li><li>ID/Passport for the Chairperson/owner/representative of the business</li><li>NSSF Forms</li></ul><p>Go the General Labour or អគ្គការងារ building, level 3 and hand in the documents.</p>		\n			<iframe frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?q=ministry%20of%20labour&amp;t=m&amp;z=14&amp;output=embed&amp;iwloc=near\" aria-label=\"ministry of labour\"></iframe>', 'NSSF Registration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1183-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:11:18', '2019-07-23 04:11:18', '', '1183', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/1183-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1846', '1', '2019-07-23 11:11:27', '2019-07-23 04:11:27', '<h2>Register through the MoC Website</h2>		\n		<p>Step by step instruction on how to register your business through the MoC website</p>		\n			<h3>Ministry of Commerce Registration</h3>		\n			<h2>1. Register as a new user</h2>		\n		<p>On the right side of the page click on \"register as a new user\"</p><p>Fill in your account details in either Khmer or English, do not click \"create an organisation\"</p><p>Click on \"Create\"</p>		\n			<a href=\"https://www.businessregistration.moc.gov.kh/\" role=\"button\">\n						Register Here\n					</a>\n			<h2>2. Reserve Your Business Name</h2>		\n		<p>On the left side click \"reserve a company name\"</p><p>Write your preferred name in both Khmer and English</p><p>The supporting documents are not compulsory</p><p>Submit when you are ready, you will be redirected to the payment page</p><p>If you have an ACLEDA account, click ACLEDA</p><p>If you do not have an ACLEDA account click cancel, then click pay later. You will have to go to ACLEDA in person and pay. </p>		\n			<h2>3. Fill out the Online Form</h2>		\n		<p>Once your name is approved you can register online. The online form requires you to upload the Memorandum and Articles of Association as well as other documents, click here for more information</p>		\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/online-form/\" role=\"button\">\n						Read more\n					</a>\n			<h2>4. File annual DeclaratioN</h2>		\n		<p>Login into the MoC website, click, maintain company, and go to file annual declaration. Follow the directions, you will need: </p><ul><li>company address</li><li>director details</li><li>shareholdings</li><li>annual return reminder details.</li><li>You also need your TIN</li><li>Tax registration date</li></ul>		\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/annual-declaration/\" role=\"button\">\n						Read more\n					</a>', 'Register through the MoC Website', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '800-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:11:27', '2019-07-23 04:11:27', '', '800', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/800-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1848', '1', '2019-07-23 11:11:35', '2019-07-23 04:11:35', '<h2>Registering with the General Department of Tax</h2>		\n		<p>To register with the tax department you need to go to the National Tax School, level 6</p>		\n		<p><strong>Tax Registration</strong></p>\n<p>You have 2 weeks once your application is approved to go to the General Department of Taxation and register.</p>\n<p>You need to bring all the documents necessary for tax registration. If your business needs to import/export, you will need to ensure you tell the tax department and get an export patent.&nbsp;</p><p>The registration process takes place at the National Tax School Building, level 6.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Once registered you will receive:</p>\n<p>the Taxpayer Identification Number : this is the number which refers you as a taxpayer with the authorities</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the Patent tax</li>\n<li>the VAT tax.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Cost of tax registration :</p>\n<p>$200 for registration, $300 for tax patent</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The National Tax School can be found here</p>\n<p></p>		\n			<iframe frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?q=National%20tax%20school%2C%20phnom%20penh&amp;t=m&amp;z=12&amp;output=embed&amp;iwloc=near\" aria-label=\"National tax school, phnom penh\"></iframe>', 'registering  with GDT', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '925-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:11:35', '2019-07-23 04:11:35', '', '925', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/925-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1850', '1', '2019-07-23 11:11:44', '2019-07-23 04:11:44', '<h2>Registering a Business</h2>		\n		<p>What you need to know to register a business in Cambodia</p>		\n			<h2>Ministry of Commerce</h2>		\n				<h3>\n					Know your Business Status\n				</h3>\n				<p>There are a variety of business statuses in Cambodia, the most common are sole proprietor, partnership and limited liability companies. Read our article for more information</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/business-status/\" role=\"button\">\n						Read more here\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-1024x683.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-300x200.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-768x512.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-640x427.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-400x267.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0835-367x245.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					Collect all the documents <br><br>\nand prerequisites\n				</h3>\n				<p>There are various documents and requirements needed before you able to register. Read our list for everything you require\n</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/documents/\" role=\"button\">\n						Documents & Prerequisites\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-1024x683.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-300x200.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-768x512.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-640x427.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-400x267.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/DSCF0253-367x245.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					Register through the MoC <br><br>\nwebsite\n				</h3>\n				<p>Once you have all the documents, you are now ready to register through the Ministry of Commerce website. There are three steps; register as a new user, reserve a name, then proceed to fill out the online form</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/elementor-746-3/\" role=\"button\">\n						Learn more\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"570\" height=\"329\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22.jpg 570w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-300x173.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-400x231.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-22-367x212.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					File Annual Declaration\n				</h3>\n				<p>The Ministry of Commerce registration process is nearly completed, the last step is to file for the annual declaration</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/annual-declaration/\" role=\"button\">\n						Learn more\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"570\" height=\"329\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23.jpg 570w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23-300x173.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23-400x231.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Layer-23-367x212.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" />											\n			<h2><a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Registering-a-Business-Checklist.pdf\">Download our Checklist Here</a></h2>		\n			<h5>Our detailed, Printable checklist will help you simplify the registration process</h5>		\n			<h2>General Department of Tax</h2>		\n				<h3>\n					Collect all the documents <br><br>\nand prerequisites\n				</h3>\n				<p>There are various documents and requirements needed to register at the General Department of Tax, many of which are the same for the MoC. Read our list for everything you require\n</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/documents-2/\" role=\"button\">\n						Documents & Prerequisites\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0158-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0158-1024x576.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0158-300x169.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0158-768x432.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0158-640x360.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0158-400x225.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0158-367x206.jpg 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n				<h3>\n					Register at the National Tax <br><br>\nSchool\n				</h3>\n				<p>The GDT does not have an online registration process at the moment so you are required to go to the National Tax School in person</p>\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/elementor-746-2-2/\" role=\"button\">\n						Read more\n					</a>\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0142-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0142-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0142-300x225.jpg 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0142-768x576.jpg 768w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0142-463x348.jpg 463w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0142-640x480.jpg 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0142-400x300.jpg 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0142-367x275.jpg 367w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMG_0142-200x150.jpg 200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n			<h2>NEED HELP?</h2>		\n			<p>Our team at Ngeay Ngeay can take care of all your registration needs</p>		\n			<a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/contact-us/\" role=\"button\">\n						Contact Us\n					</a>', 'Registering a Business Checklist good', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '998-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:11:44', '2019-07-23 04:11:44', '', '998', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/998-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1853', '1', '2019-07-23 11:11:59', '2019-07-23 04:11:59', '<h2>Required Accounting</h2>		\n		<p>Once you register your business one of the most important requirements is clear and proper accounting.</p>		\n		<p><strong>Small Taxpayers (Sole Proprietors &amp; Partnerships)</strong></p><p>The requirements for small taxpayers are significantly less than they are for medium and large taxpayers. Small Taxpayers are required to have three books:</p><p><em>Expenses Day Book</em></p><p>This is the gathering of all the operational expenses made by the company, so basically everything that it buys. It can refer to: goods or services, raw materials, employee wages, utility bills…. This record has to be completed daily.</p><p><em>Sales Day Book</em></p><p>The Sales day book, also a daily record, refers to all the goods and services sold by the company.</p><p><em>Inventory Book</em></p><p>The inventory book is the count of the inventory of the business.</p><p>Other suggested but not legally required books are:</p><p><em>Accounts Receivable</em></p><p>This is any money that is owed to you</p><p><em>Accounts Payable</em></p><p>This is any money that you owe</p><p><em>Assets Book</em></p><p>Any equipment, furniture or machinery you buy that is over $100</p><p><strong>Medium &amp; Large Taxpayers</strong></p><p>As the tax filing that is required for medium and large taxpayers is significantly more complex than it is for small taxpayers we strongly recommend that you use official accounting procedures such as CIFRS and use a system such as quickbooks, xero or banhji.</p><p>If you are new to book keeping and accounting, we recommend that you hire a professional to help you with these. See here.</p>', 'Required accounting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1193-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:11:59', '2019-07-23 04:11:59', '', '1193', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/1193-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1855', '1', '2019-07-23 11:12:08', '2019-07-23 04:12:08', '<h2>Salaries &amp; Compensation</h2>		\n		<p>Everything you need to know about salaries and compensation in Cambodia</p>		\n		<p><strong>Fortnightly Payments</strong></p><p>As of January 1<sup>st</sup>, 2019, all businesses are required to pay their employees two times per month. The first payment shall be 50% of the employees’ net wage and the second payment shall contain the remaining net wages plus any benefits owed.</p><p><strong>Minimum Wage</strong></p><p>There is no official minimum wage in Cambodia, however the general consensus is that the minimum wage should be set at the Garment Industry minimum wage which is $182/month for a 48-hour week.</p><p><strong>Overtime</strong></p><p>Overtime is classified as any hours above the normal working hours, which at a minimum must be no more than 9 hours/day, and no more than 48 hours per week. Any hours worked above these hours or the hours agreed upon employment are deemed to be overtime.</p><p>Overtime must be paid at 150% of wages or 200% of wages if worked between 10pm and 5am.</p><p>Additionally, workers may be entitled to days in lieu, if they are need to work on a typical rest day, the employees are entitled to take another day off.</p><p><strong>Public Holidays</strong></p><p>All employees are entitled to public holiday leave according the public holiday sub-decree issued by the government. In the case a public holiday is on a Sunday, employees are entitled to take the following Monday off work.</p><p>If businesses are required to open on public holidays, employees can work voluntarily but are entitled to pay of 200% of their normal wage.</p>', 'Salaries & Compensation', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1196-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:12:08', '2019-07-23 04:12:08', '', '1196', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/1196-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1857', '1', '2019-07-23 11:12:16', '2019-07-23 04:12:16', '<h2>Seniority Payments</h2>		\n		<p>The seniority payment (Prakas 443) is quite complex and there are some issues that are not 100% clear at this date.</p>		\n		<p><strong>Seniority payments vs Severance Payments</strong></p><p>There are now two terms for severance payments in the updated Labour Law, seniority payments and severance payments. Severance payments refer to <a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/contracts/\">Fixed Duration contracts</a> (FDC). Seniority payments refer to <a href=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/contracts/\">Unfixed Duration contracts</a> (UDC).</p><p><strong>Severance Payments (Fixed Duration Contracts)</strong></p><p>For employees under fixed duration contracts, a severance pay of 5% of the total wages due throughout the contract must be paid at the completion or termination of the contract.</p><p><strong>Seniority Payments (Unfixed Duration Contracts)</strong></p><p>Employees on unfixed duration contracts are entitled to seniority payments equal to 15 days of wages and fringe benefits per year. This is to be made over two payments over the year:</p><p>1<sup>st</sup> payment (June): 7.5 days of wages and fringe benefits to be paid each year</p><p>2<sup>nd</sup> payment: (December): 7.5 days of wages and fringe benefits to be paid each year</p><p><strong>Back Pay of Seniority Payments</strong></p><p>Employees who have been employed prior to 2019 are entitled to back pay of seniority payments for the course of their employment, however this is capped at a maximum of 6 month of the average base wage in each year of employment.</p><p>For the non-TGF industry, the back pay has been delayed until December 2021.</p><p><strong>Textile, Garment and Footwear (TGF) Industry</strong></p><p>For the textile, garment and footwear (TGF) manufacturing industry, employees are entitled to 30 days of back pay each year (to a maximum of 6 months).</p><p>Back pay is to be paid in two installments over the course of the year; therefore an employee that commenced employment before 2019 is entitled to receive two payments in June; 1 back pay payment of 15 days and one seniority payment of 7.5 days of wages.</p><p>The back pay of seniority payments begins in 2019 with the first payment due in June 2019.</p><p><strong>Non-TGF Industry</strong></p><p>For companies not in the TGF industry the back pay of seniority payments are equal to 6 days of wages per year of employment (to a maximum of 6 months). The timing of these payments are 3 days in June and 3 days in December.</p><p>For the non-TGF industry, the back pay has been delayed until December 2021.</p>', 'Seniority Payments', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1198-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 11:12:16', '2019-07-23 04:12:16', '', '1198', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/1198-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
