 span=\"1\">\n							</colgroup>\n		<thead>\n			<tr>\n			<th>\n							Withholding Tax						\n				</th>\n			<th>\n							Rate						\n				</th>\n						</tr>\n		</thead><tbody><tr>\n				<td data-title=\"Withholding Tax\">\n					Rent				\n		</td>		<td data-title=\"Rate\" colspan=\"2\">\n					10%				\n		</td></tr><tr>\n				<td data-title=\"Withholding Tax\">\n					Services				\n		</td>		<td data-title=\"Rate\">\n					15%				\n		</td></tr><tr>\n				<td data-title=\"Withholding Tax\">\n					Interest Payments (excluding interest paid by a domestic bank)				\n		</td>		<td data-title=\"Rate\">\n					15%				\n		</td></tr><tr>\n				<td data-title=\"Withholding Tax\">\n					Royalties (Dividends)				\n		</td>		<td data-title=\"Rate\">\n					15%				\n		</td></tr><tr>\n				<td data-title=\"Withholding Tax\">\n					Interest paid on fixed term deposit (by domestic bank)				\n		</td>		<td data-title=\"Rate\">\n					6%				\n		</td></tr><tr>\n				<td data-title=\"Withholding Tax\">\n					Interest paid on non-fixed term deposit (by a domestic bank)				\n		</td>		<td data-title=\"Rate\">\n					4%				\n		</td></tr>\n			</tbody>\n		</table>\n		<table>\n						<colgroup>\n								<col span=\"1\">\n							</colgroup>\n		<thead>\n			<tr>\n			<th>\n							Other Taxes						\n				</th>\n			<th>\n							Rate						\n				</th>\n						</tr>\n		</thead><tbody><tr>\n				<td data-title=\"Other Taxes\">\n					Fringe Benefit Tax				\n		</td>		<td data-title=\"Rate\" colspan=\"2\">\n					20%				\n		</td></tr><tr>\n				<td data-title=\"Other Taxes\">\n					Public Lighting Tax				\n		</td>		<td data-title=\"Rate\">\n					3%				\n		</td></tr><tr>\n				<td data-title=\"Other Taxes\">\n					Accomodation Tax				\n		</td>		<td data-title=\"Rate\">\n					2%				\n		</td></tr><tr>\n				<td data-title=\"Other Taxes\">\n					Tax on Property Rental				\n		</td>		<td data-title=\"Rate\">\n					10%				\n		</td></tr>\n			</tbody>\n		</table>\n		<table>\n						<colgroup>\n								<col span=\"1\">\n							</colgroup>\n		<thead>\n			<tr>\n			<th>\n							NSSF						\n				</th>\n			<th>\n							Rate						\n				</th>\n						</tr>\n		</thead><tbody><tr>\n				<td data-title=\"NSSF\">\n					Occupational Risk Scheme				\n		</td>		<td data-title=\"Rate\" colspan=\"2\">\n					0.8% of wage				\n		</td></tr><tr>\n				<td data-title=\"NSSF\">\n					Health Care Scheme				\n		</td>		<td data-title=\"Rate\">\n					2.6% of wage				\n		</td></tr>\n			</tbody>\n		</table>\n		<p><strong>1. Minimum Tax</strong></p><p>Profit tax prepayment:</p><p>Every month, you need to pay the rate of 1% on your turnover of the previous month inclusive of all taxes, except for VAT.</p><p><strong>2. Withholding Tax</strong></p><p>Rental : 10%</p><p>Labour : 15%</p><p><strong>3. Value Added Tax (VAT)</strong></p><p>The standard rate of VAT is 10%. It applies to all supplies, excluding exports and non-taxable supplies. Exported goods from Cambodia and services consumed outside Cambodia are not subject to VAT tax. The VAT is charged to the client and then paid to the government.</p><p><strong>4. Salary Tax and Tax on Fringe Benefit</strong></p><p>A company that has employees has to withhold tax before paying the employees and to pay it to the tax administration the month after the salary is paid. The rate depends on the employee salary, as listed below.</p><p>Monthly salary (Riels) Rate:</p><p>0 – 1,200,000                          0%</p><p>1,200,001 – 2,000,000          5%</p><p>2,000,001 – 8,500,000          10%</p><p>8,500,001 – 12,500,000        15%</p><p>12,500,001 – upwards          20%</p><p>You can download the <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.gdt.project.salarytax2018&amp;hl=en\">Salary Tax 2018 App</a> here, it can calculate your salary tax</p><p><strong>5. Public Lighting Tax</strong></p><p>This is a tax on all alcohol and cigarettes. The rate is 3% of all sales.</p><p><strong>NSSF Rates</strong></p><p>There are two contributions for the National Social Security Fund that are to be made each month by the employer.</p><p><strong>The Occupational Risk Scheme</strong></p><p>The rate for occupational risk is 0.8% of the workers gross wage.</p><p><strong>The Health Care Scheme</strong></p><p>The rate for the Health Care Scheme is 2.6% of the workers gross wage.</p><p>All workers are to be registered with the NSSF within 3 days of beginning employment.</p><p>NSSF payment deadline: 15<sup>th</sup> of each month</p>', 'Tax & NSSF Rates', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1189-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 16:28:15', '2019-07-23 09:28:15', '', '1189', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/1189-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
