INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1931', '1', '2019-07-23 17:46:37', '2019-07-23 10:46:37', '<h2>The Art of Delegation</h2>\nDelegation is a critical skill for a leader but it is difficult to learn, and often is best learnt through experience. Delegation is an art but there are some principles that will help you improve faster.\n\nFor many entrepreneurs this is one of the hardest skills to learn, as entrepreneurs and business owners will often feel like that they are losing control of their business and cannot trust people with important tasks. But delegation is a critical skill, as the business grows, the owner can no longer do everything and needs to be able to trust their staff to take on responsibility.\n\nBut for delegation to be successful the owner needs to delegate in a meaningful, purposeful way. Here are some steps we like to think about when delegating tasks:\n\n<strong>Choose the right tasks</strong>\n\nYou should be doing the tasks that ONLY YOU can do, and the tasks that are most critical for the business. If there are tasks that do not interest you, or that you are not good at, these are the tasks that you should be delegating.\n\n<strong>Choose the right person</strong>\n\nThink about what the task involves, and the skills and behaviours needed to complete the task and choose the person most suited to that. You will need to trust the person to do a good job, so choosing the right person is critical.\n\n<strong>Give clear instructions and directions</strong>\n\nThis does not mean mapping out every single detail, but providing enough direction so the person can complete the task but does not feel like they are being micro managed.\n\n<strong>Follow up</strong>\n\nEnsure that you have given timelines, and then one of the most important aspects of delegation is following up and ensuring the task is completed and you have provided feedback.\n\nDelegation is a difficult skill and takes time to get right, most managers and business owners we speak to are still learning the balance between maintaining control without micro managing. However, with time and dedication, delegation can allow the entrepreneur to work on the business, and not in the business.', 'The Art of Delegation', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'elementor-1404-3-2', '', '', '2019-07-23 18:20:24', '2019-07-23 11:20:24', '', '0', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/?p=1931', '0', 'post', '', '0');
