INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1934', '1', '2019-07-23 17:55:33', '2019-07-23 10:55:33', '<h2>Start with WHY</h2>\nCreating a team of loyal followers and a company with loyal customers is incredibly difficult and there are not many leaders or companies that have really achieved this\n\nCompanies like Apple, Harley Davidson or Brown Coffee, have started something special with incredibly loyal customers, followers and teams.\n\nThese companies and leaders are able to inspire their employees to go through all the hard times with them and come out the other end, how do these companies and leaders achieve this? Money? Benefits? Extra Holidays? These are nice, but they do not inspire loyalty, when they can no longer get more money or more benefits, employees will leave. So how do they do it? These companies and leaders start with WHY.\n\nIn Simon Sinek’s now famous TED talk, he talks about a three layer circle, WHY being at the center, how in the next ring, and what in the outer circle.\n\n<img width=\"408\" height=\"343\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WHY.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WHY.png 408w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WHY-300x252.png 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WHY-400x336.png 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/WHY-367x309.png 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 408px) 100vw, 408px\">\n\nMost companies and leaders can answer the WHAT, this is easy, describing your products and industry, some leaders can answer the HOW, your value proposition, unique selling point and add ons. But the WHY? The reason the company exists, WHY is the company doing this? WHY should anyone (staff, customers, beneficiaries) care?\n\nAt Ngeay Ngeay, we will often ask business owners to describe their core focus in two parts:\n\nOne sentence on their niche, or really what we’re asking is the WHAT &amp; HOW, every business owner we’ve worked with is able to tell us this easily. The second part is harder, we ask them, what is the businesses (or the leaders) passion, or cause, or purpose. This is the WHY, 90% of the businesses we work with have a lot of trouble answering this.\n\nSinek, says that most companies will start with the WHAT, then move on to the HOW and sometimes they get to WHY, but great companies will start with WHY as this provides all the reason WHY anyone should follow them, staff or customers. With this in the mind, the WHAT is the proof that belief.\n\nCan you clearly articulate the WHY of your business? Do your staff now your WHY?\n\nIf you need help providing direction for your business, our team can help\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7zFeuSagktM', 'Start with WHY', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1931-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-07-23 17:55:33', '2019-07-23 10:55:33', '', '1931', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/2019/07/23/1931-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
