INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1937', '1', '2019-07-23 18:10:53', '2019-07-23 11:10:53', '<h2>The Four Quadrant of Time Management</h2>\nWhen running a business, it can feel like you have a thousand jobs to do, and they all have to be done now. How do you make sure you get the right things done at the right time?\n\nStephen Covey’s famous time management matrix is a great way to get a handle on your tasks and ensure you are spending your time on the right things. The concept is that everything you do in life can classified by its urgency (urgent or not urgent) and its importance (important or not important). By using these four classifications we can create a matrix.\n\nQuadrant 1: Urgent &amp; Important\n\nQuadrant 2: Not urgent &amp; important\n\nQuadrant 3: Urgent &amp; not important\n\nQuadrant 4: Not urgent &amp; not important\n\n<img width=\"485\" height=\"452\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/4Quadrant.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/4Quadrant.png 485w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/4Quadrant-300x280.png 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/4Quadrant-400x373.png 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/4Quadrant-367x342.png 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 485px) 100vw, 485px\">\n\n<strong>Urgent &amp; Important</strong>\n\nThis category is for emergencies, crises, hard deadlines. This section is for everything that is very important and has very strict deadlines, these are items that should not be ignored. This quadrant is often where business owners spend their most time, this is one of the primary reasons for burn out in business owners, they are spending too much time in emergency mode and not enough time in planning &amp; deep work mode.\n\n<strong>Important &amp; Not Urgent</strong>\n\n<strong>This is the quadrant you want to spend the majority of your time. </strong>\n\nThis quadrant is for deep work, planning, improvement, strategies etc. This is where you work on developing processes that will save you time in the future, or meeting potential clients, or learning about business or training staff. Spending more time here, means less time spent in quadrant 1, as emergencies and crises will be avoided and hard deadlines will be easier to reach.\n\n<strong>Not Important and Urgent</strong>\n\nWe can often fall victim to spending a lot of time in this quadrant and feeling like we are getting a lot done. This means answering phones, messaging people, answering emails as they come in, getting interrupted in the office. When you spend a lot of time in this section, you FEEL BUSY, but in reality, you are not really achieving much and will likely soon find yourself in quadrant 1 dealing with an emergency.\n\n<strong>Not Urgent and Not Important</strong>\n\nThese are the time-wasting activities, they offer no benefit and we should try to cut them out as much as possible. Examples like mindless facebook or websurfing, watching too much tv etc. Don’t confuse dedicated relaxing time with this quadrant, this quadrant is about the times where you are mindlessly wasting time, or procrastinating.\n\n<strong>So how do we spend more time in Quadrant 2?</strong>\n\nThere are 4 simple steps to put more energy into quadrant 2. These steps are simple but not necessarily easy and require some discipline.\n<ol>\n 	<li>Identify your quadrant 2 tasks</li>\n 	<li>Free up time for quadrant 2 tasks (stop notifications for emails, facebook etc)</li>\n 	<li>Schedule quadrant 2 tasks (start with 1-2 hours each day and eventually move to ½ day scheduled for quadrant 2 tasks)</li>\n 	<li>Reduce quadrant 1 (as you do more quadrant 2 tasks, the amount of quadrant 1 tasks should slowly start reducing)</li>\n</ol>', 'Four Quadrant Time Management', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'elementor-1404-3-3', '', '', '2019-07-23 18:20:13', '2019-07-23 11:20:13', '', '0', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/?p=1937', '0', 'post', '', '0');
