INSERT INTO `nge_posts` VALUES('1950', '1', '2019-07-24 11:57:21', '2019-07-24 04:57:21', '<h2>The Business Model Canvas</h2>\nUnderstanding your business model in 1 page\n\nThe Business Model Canvas is a 1-page tool that allows you to map out your business model and understand the most important parts of your business. Understanding your business model is very important, whether you have a business idea, are starting a business, or are developing a new product.\n\nListen to Chan Chamsophea talk about how understanding her business model helped her grow her business.\n\nhttps://youtu.be/klyqjNp6xwQ\n\nThe Business Model Canvas consists of 9 sections; the value proposition, customer segments, channels, customer relationships, key partners, key resources, key activities, and revenue and costs\n\n<img width=\"760\" height=\"487\" src=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Business-Model-Canvas-Annoted-760.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Business-Model-Canvas-Annoted-760.png 760w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Business-Model-Canvas-Annoted-760-300x192.png 300w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Business-Model-Canvas-Annoted-760-640x410.png 640w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Business-Model-Canvas-Annoted-760-400x256.png 400w, http://ngeayngeay.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Business-Model-Canvas-Annoted-760-367x235.png 367w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\">\n\nBy mapping out these key parts of your business you can clearly see what the most important aspects of your business are, additionally, if you have an established business it gives you a starting point to be able modify and grow your business model. Additionally, mapping out new products and their specific business model can help you clarify how the product will fit into your existing model. Business models are rarely fixed and change as the market changes and new products and new technology evolves. Businesses that do not adapt their model will often struggle to survive long term.\n\nIn the <a href=\"http://learn.ngeayngeay.co\">e-learning section</a> of our website we have 11 part series that takes you through the Business Model Canvas, step-by-step, so you can map out your model, and understand how you can use the Business Model Canvas to grow your business.&nbsp;', 'The Business Model Canvas', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'elementor-1404-3-3-2-2', '', '', '2019-07-24 13:06:44', '2019-07-24 06:06:44', '', '0', 'http://maskred.com/BIGkeenProject/BK_ngeayngeay/?p=1950', '0', 'post', '', '0');
